8414 static void DiagnoseNarrowingInInitList(Sema &S,
8415  const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS,
8416  QualType PreNarrowingType,
8417  QualType EntityType,
8418  const Expr *PostInit);
8419 
8420 static void CheckC23ConstexprInitConversion(Sema &S, QualType FromType,
8421  QualType ToType, Expr *Init);
8422 
8423 /// Provide warnings when std::move is used on construction.
8424 static void CheckMoveOnConstruction(Sema &S, const Expr *InitExpr,
8425  bool IsReturnStmt) {
8426  if (!InitExpr)
8427  return;
8428 
8429  if (S.inTemplateInstantiation())
8430  return;
8431 
8432  QualType DestType = InitExpr->getType();
8433  if (!DestType->isRecordType())
8434  return;
8435 
8436  unsigned DiagID = 0;
8437  if (IsReturnStmt) {
8438  const CXXConstructExpr *CCE =
8439  dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(InitExpr->IgnoreParens());
8440  if (!CCE || CCE->getNumArgs() != 1)
8441  return;
8442 
8443  if (!CCE->getConstructor()->isCopyOrMoveConstructor())
8444  return;
8445 
8446  InitExpr = CCE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImpCasts();
8447  }
8448 
8449  // Find the std::move call and get the argument.
8450  const CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(InitExpr->IgnoreParens());
8451  if (!CE || !CE->isCallToStdMove())
8452  return;
8453 
8454  const Expr *Arg = CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImplicit();
8455 
8456  if (IsReturnStmt) {
8457  const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Arg->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
8458  if (!DRE || DRE->refersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture())
8459  return;
8460 
8461  const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
8462  if (!VD || !VD->hasLocalStorage())
8463  return;
8464 
8465  // __block variables are not moved implicitly.
8466  if (VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>())
8467  return;
8468 
8469  QualType SourceType = VD->getType();
8470  if (!SourceType->isRecordType())
8471  return;
8472 
8473  if (!S.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestType, SourceType)) {
8474  return;
8475  }
8476 
8477  // If we're returning a function parameter, copy elision
8478  // is not possible.
8479  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD))
8480  DiagID = diag::warn_redundant_move_on_return;
8481  else
8482  DiagID = diag::warn_pessimizing_move_on_return;
8483  } else {
8484  DiagID = diag::warn_pessimizing_move_on_initialization;
8485  const Expr *ArgStripped = Arg->IgnoreImplicit()->IgnoreParens();
8486  if (!ArgStripped->isPRValue() || !ArgStripped->getType()->isRecordType())
8487  return;
8488  }
8489 
8490  S.Diag(CE->getBeginLoc(), DiagID);
8491 
8492  // Get all the locations for a fix-it. Don't emit the fix-it if any location
8493  // is within a macro.
8494  SourceLocation CallBegin = CE->getCallee()->getBeginLoc();
8495  if (CallBegin.isMacroID())
8496  return;
8497  SourceLocation RParen = CE->getRParenLoc();
8498  if (RParen.isMacroID())
8499  return;
8500  SourceLocation LParen;
8501  SourceLocation ArgLoc = Arg->getBeginLoc();
8502 
8503  // Special testing for the argument location. Since the fix-it needs the
8504  // location right before the argument, the argument location can be in a
8505  // macro only if it is at the beginning of the macro.
8506  while (ArgLoc.isMacroID() &&
8507  S.getSourceManager().isAtStartOfImmediateMacroExpansion(ArgLoc)) {
8508  ArgLoc = S.getSourceManager().getImmediateExpansionRange(ArgLoc).getBegin();
8509  }
8510 
8511  if (LParen.isMacroID())
8512  return;
8513 
8514  LParen = ArgLoc.getLocWithOffset(-1);
8515 
8516  S.Diag(CE->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_remove_move)
8517  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(CallBegin, LParen))
8518  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(RParen, RParen));
8519 }
8520 
8521 static void CheckForNullPointerDereference(Sema &S, const Expr *E) {
8522  // Check to see if we are dereferencing a null pointer. If so, this is
8523  // undefined behavior, so warn about it. This only handles the pattern
8524  // "*null", which is a very syntactic check.
8525  if (const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E->IgnoreParenCasts()))
8526  if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Deref &&
8527  UO->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParenCasts()->
8528  isNullPointerConstant(S.Context, Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull)) {
8529  S.DiagRuntimeBehavior(UO->getOperatorLoc(), UO,
8530  S.PDiag(diag::warn_binding_null_to_reference)
8531  << UO->getSubExpr()->getSourceRange());
8532  }
8533 }
8534 
8535 MaterializeTemporaryExpr *
8536 Sema::CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(QualType T, Expr *Temporary,
8537  bool BoundToLvalueReference) {
8538  auto MTE = new (Context)
8539  MaterializeTemporaryExpr(T, Temporary, BoundToLvalueReference);
8540 
8541  // Order an ExprWithCleanups for lifetime marks.
8542  //
8543  // TODO: It'll be good to have a single place to check the access of the
8544  // destructor and generate ExprWithCleanups for various uses. Currently these
8545  // are done in both CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr and MaybeBindToTemporary,
8546  // but there may be a chance to merge them.
8547  Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(false);
8548  if (isInLifetimeExtendingContext()) {
8549  auto &Record = ExprEvalContexts.back();
8550  Record.ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps.push_back(MTE);
8551  }
8552  return MTE;
8553 }
8554 
8555 ExprResult Sema::TemporaryMaterializationConversion(Expr *E) {
8556  // In C++98, we don't want to implicitly create an xvalue.
8557  // FIXME: This means that AST consumers need to deal with "prvalues" that
8558  // denote materialized temporaries. Maybe we should add another ValueKind
8559  // for "xvalue pretending to be a prvalue" for C++98 support.
8560  if (!E->isPRValue() || !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
8561  return E;
8562 
8563  // C++1z [conv.rval]/1: T shall be a complete type.
8564  // FIXME: Does this ever matter (can we form a prvalue of incomplete type)?
8565  // If so, we should check for a non-abstract class type here too.
8566  QualType T = E->getType();
8567  if (RequireCompleteType(E->getExprLoc(), T, diag::err_incomplete_type))
8568  return ExprError();
8569 
8570  return CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(E->getType(), E, false);
8571 }
8572 
8573 ExprResult Sema::PerformQualificationConversion(Expr *E, QualType Ty,
8574  ExprValueKind VK,
8575  CheckedConversionKind CCK) {
8576 
8577  CastKind CK = CK_NoOp;
8578 
8579  if (VK == VK_PRValue) {
8580  auto PointeeTy = Ty->getPointeeType();
8581  auto ExprPointeeTy = E->getType()->getPointeeType();
8582  if (!PointeeTy.isNull() &&
8583  PointeeTy.getAddressSpace() != ExprPointeeTy.getAddressSpace())
8584  CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
8585  } else if (Ty.getAddressSpace() != E->getType().getAddressSpace()) {
8586  CK = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
8587  }
8588 
8589  return ImpCastExprToType(E, Ty, CK, VK, /*BasePath=*/nullptr, CCK);
8590 }
8591 
8592 ExprResult InitializationSequence::Perform(Sema &S,
8593  const InitializedEntity &Entity,
8594  const InitializationKind &Kind,
8595  MultiExprArg Args,
8596  QualType *ResultType) {
8597  if (Failed()) {
8598  Diagnose(S, Entity, Kind, Args);
8599  return ExprError();
8600  }
8601  if (!ZeroInitializationFixit.empty()) {
8602  const Decl *D = Entity.getDecl();
8603  const auto *VD = dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(D);
8604  QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
8605 
8606  // The initialization would have succeeded with this fixit. Since the fixit
8607  // is on the error, we need to build a valid AST in this case, so this isn't
8608  // handled in the Failed() branch above.
8609  if (!DestType->isRecordType() && VD && VD->isConstexpr()) {
8610  // Use a more useful diagnostic for constexpr variables.
8611  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_constexpr_var_requires_const_init)
8612  << VD
8613  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(ZeroInitializationFixitLoc,
8614  ZeroInitializationFixit);
8615  } else {
8616  unsigned DiagID = diag::err_default_init_const;
8617  if (S.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && D && D->hasAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
8618  DiagID = diag::ext_default_init_const;
8619 
8620  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), DiagID)
8621  << DestType << (bool)DestType->getAs<RecordType>()
8622  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(ZeroInitializationFixitLoc,
8623  ZeroInitializationFixit);
8624  }
8625  }
8626 
8627  if (getKind() == DependentSequence) {
8628  // If the declaration is a non-dependent, incomplete array type
8629  // that has an initializer, then its type will be completed once
8630  // the initializer is instantiated.
8631  if (ResultType && !Entity.getType()->isDependentType() &&
8632  Args.size() == 1) {
8633  QualType DeclType = Entity.getType();
8634  if (const IncompleteArrayType *ArrayT
8635  = S.Context.getAsIncompleteArrayType(DeclType)) {
8636  // FIXME: We don't currently have the ability to accurately
8637  // compute the length of an initializer list without
8638  // performing full type-checking of the initializer list
8639  // (since we have to determine where braces are implicitly
8640  // introduced and such). So, we fall back to making the array
8641  // type a dependently-sized array type with no specified
8642  // bound.
8643  if (isa<InitListExpr>((Expr *)Args[0])) {
8644  SourceRange Brackets;
8645 
8646  // Scavange the location of the brackets from the entity, if we can.
8647  if (auto *DD = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclaratorDecl>(Entity.getDecl())) {
8648  if (TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = DD->getTypeSourceInfo()) {
8649  TypeLoc TL = TInfo->getTypeLoc();
8650  if (IncompleteArrayTypeLoc ArrayLoc =
8651  TL.getAs<IncompleteArrayTypeLoc>())
8652  Brackets = ArrayLoc.getBracketsRange();
8653  }
8654  }
8655 
8656  *ResultType
8657  = S.Context.getDependentSizedArrayType(ArrayT->getElementType(),
8658  /*NumElts=*/nullptr,
8659  ArrayT->getSizeModifier(),
8660  ArrayT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
8661  Brackets);
8662  }
8663 
8664  }
8665  }
8666  if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Direct &&
8667  !Kind.isExplicitCast()) {
8668  // Rebuild the ParenListExpr.
8669  SourceRange ParenRange = Kind.getParenOrBraceRange();
8670  return S.ActOnParenListExpr(ParenRange.getBegin(), ParenRange.getEnd(),
8671  Args);
8672  }
8673  assert(Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Copy ||
8674  Kind.isExplicitCast() ||
8675  Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_DirectList);
8676  return ExprResult(Args[0]);
8677  }
8678 
8679  // No steps means no initialization.
8680  if (Steps.empty())
8681  return ExprResult((Expr *)nullptr);
8682 
8683  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Entity.getType()->isReferenceType() &&
8684  Args.size() == 1 && isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]) &&
8685  !Entity.isParamOrTemplateParamKind()) {
8686  // Produce a C++98 compatibility warning if we are initializing a reference
8687  // from an initializer list. For parameters, we produce a better warning
8688  // elsewhere.
8689  Expr *Init = Args[0];
8690  S.Diag(Init->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cxx98_compat_reference_list_init)
8691  << Init->getSourceRange();
8692  }
8693 
8694  if (S.getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt && Args.size() == 1 &&
8695  isa<PredefinedExpr>(Args[0]) && Entity.getType()->isArrayType()) {
8696  // Produce a Microsoft compatibility warning when initializing from a
8697  // predefined expression since MSVC treats predefined expressions as string
8698  // literals.
8699  Expr *Init = Args[0];
8700  S.Diag(Init->getBeginLoc(), diag::ext_init_from_predefined) << Init;
8701  }
8702 
8703  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.11.1. atomic variables can be initialized in global scope
8704  QualType ETy = Entity.getType();
8705  bool HasGlobalAS = ETy.hasAddressSpace() &&
8706  ETy.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_global;
8707 
8708  if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion >= 200 &&
8709  ETy->isAtomicType() && !HasGlobalAS &&
8710  Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Variable && Args.size() > 0) {
8711  S.Diag(Args[0]->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_opencl_atomic_init)
8712  << 1
8713  << SourceRange(Entity.getDecl()->getBeginLoc(), Args[0]->getEndLoc());
8714  return ExprError();
8715  }
8716 
8717  QualType DestType = Entity.getType().getNonReferenceType();
8718  // FIXME: Ugly hack around the fact that Entity.getType() is not
8719  // the same as Entity.getDecl()->getType() in cases involving type merging,
8720  // and we want latter when it makes sense.
8721  if (ResultType)
8722  *ResultType = Entity.getDecl() ? Entity.getDecl()->getType() :
8723  Entity.getType();
8724 
8725  ExprResult CurInit((Expr *)nullptr);
8726  SmallVector<Expr*, 4> ArrayLoopCommonExprs;
8727 
8728  // HLSL allows vector initialization to function like list initialization, but
8729  // use the syntax of a C++-like constructor.
8730  bool IsHLSLVectorInit = S.getLangOpts().HLSL && DestType->isExtVectorType() &&
8731  isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
8732  (void)IsHLSLVectorInit;
8733 
8734  // For initialization steps that start with a single initializer,
8735  // grab the only argument out the Args and place it into the "current"
8736  // initializer.
8737  switch (Steps.front().Kind) {
8738  case SK_ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction:
8739  case SK_CastDerivedToBasePRValue:
8740  case SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue:
8741  case SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue:
8742  case SK_BindReference:
8743  case SK_BindReferenceToTemporary:
8744  case SK_FinalCopy:
8745  case SK_ExtraneousCopyToTemporary:
8746  case SK_UserConversion:
8747  case SK_QualificationConversionLValue:
8748  case SK_QualificationConversionXValue:
8749  case SK_QualificationConversionPRValue:
8750  case SK_FunctionReferenceConversion:
8751  case SK_AtomicConversion:
8752  case SK_ConversionSequence:
8753  case SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing:
8754  case SK_ListInitialization:
8755  case SK_UnwrapInitList:
8756  case SK_RewrapInitList:
8757  case SK_CAssignment:
8758  case SK_StringInit:
8759  case SK_ObjCObjectConversion:
8760  case SK_ArrayLoopIndex:
8761  case SK_ArrayLoopInit:
8762  case SK_ArrayInit:
8763  case SK_GNUArrayInit:
8764  case SK_ParenthesizedArrayInit:
8765  case SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore:
8766  case SK_PassByIndirectRestore:
8767  case SK_ProduceObjCObject:
8768  case SK_StdInitializerList:
8769  case SK_OCLSamplerInit:
8770  case SK_OCLZeroOpaqueType: {
8771  assert(Args.size() == 1 || IsHLSLVectorInit);
8772  CurInit = Args[0];
8773  if (!CurInit.get()) return ExprError();
8774  break;
8775  }
8776 
8777  case SK_ConstructorInitialization:
8778  case SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList:
8779  case SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall:
8780  case SK_ZeroInitialization:
8781  case SK_ParenthesizedListInit:
8782  break;
8783  }
8784 
8785  // Promote from an unevaluated context to an unevaluated list context in
8786  // C++11 list-initialization; we need to instantiate entities usable in
8787  // constant expressions here in order to perform narrowing checks =(
8788  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Evaluated(
8789  S, EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList,
8790  CurInit.get() && isa<InitListExpr>(CurInit.get()));
8791 
8792  // C++ [class.abstract]p2:
8793  // no objects of an abstract class can be created except as subobjects
8794  // of a class derived from it
8795  auto checkAbstractType = [&](QualType T) -> bool {
8796  if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base ||
8797  Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Delegating)
8798  return false;
8799  return S.RequireNonAbstractType(Kind.getLocation(), T,
8800  diag::err_allocation_of_abstract_type);
8801  };
8802 
8803  // Walk through the computed steps for the initialization sequence,
8804  // performing the specified conversions along the way.
8805  bool ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit = false;
8806  for (step_iterator Step = step_begin(), StepEnd = step_end();
8807  Step != StepEnd; ++Step) {
8808  if (CurInit.isInvalid())
8809  return ExprError();
8810 
8811  QualType SourceType = CurInit.get() ? CurInit.get()->getType() : QualType();
8812 
8813  switch (Step->Kind) {
8814  case SK_ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction:
8815  // Overload resolution determined which function invoke; update the
8816  // initializer to reflect that choice.
8817  S.CheckAddressOfMemberAccess(CurInit.get(), Step->Function.FoundDecl);
8818  if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Step->Function.FoundDecl, Kind.getLocation()))
8819  return ExprError();
8820  CurInit = S.FixOverloadedFunctionReference(CurInit,
8821  Step->Function.FoundDecl,
8822  Step->Function.Function);
8823  // We might get back another placeholder expression if we resolved to a
8824  // builtin.
8825  if (!CurInit.isInvalid())
8826  CurInit = S.CheckPlaceholderExpr(CurInit.get());
8827  break;
8828 
8829  case SK_CastDerivedToBasePRValue:
8830  case SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue:
8831  case SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue: {
8832  // We have a derived-to-base cast that produces either an rvalue or an
8833  // lvalue. Perform that cast.
8834 
8835  CXXCastPath BasePath;
8836 
8837  // Casts to inaccessible base classes are allowed with C-style casts.
8838  bool IgnoreBaseAccess = Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast();
8839  if (S.CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(
8840  SourceType, Step->Type, CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc(),
8841  CurInit.get()->getSourceRange(), &BasePath, IgnoreBaseAccess))
8842  return ExprError();
8843 
8844  ExprValueKind VK =
8845  Step->Kind == SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue
8846  ? VK_LValue
8847  : (Step->Kind == SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue ? VK_XValue
8848  : VK_PRValue);
8849  CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(S.Context, Step->Type,
8850  CK_DerivedToBase, CurInit.get(),
8851  &BasePath, VK, FPOptionsOverride());
8852  break;
8853  }
8854 
8855  case SK_BindReference:
8856  // Reference binding does not have any corresponding ASTs.
8857 
8858  // Check exception specifications
8859  if (S.CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(CurInit.get(), DestType))
8860  return ExprError();
8861 
8862  // We don't check for e.g. function pointers here, since address
8863  // availability checks should only occur when the function first decays
8864  // into a pointer or reference.
8865  if (CurInit.get()->getType()->isFunctionProtoType()) {
8866  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(CurInit.get()->IgnoreParens())) {
8867  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
8868  if (!S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FD, /*Complain=*/true,
8869  DRE->getBeginLoc()))
8870  return ExprError();
8871  }
8872  }
8873  }
8874 
8875  CheckForNullPointerDereference(S, CurInit.get());
8876  break;
8877 
8878  case SK_BindReferenceToTemporary: {
8879  // Make sure the "temporary" is actually an rvalue.
8880  assert(CurInit.get()->isPRValue() && "not a temporary");
8881 
8882  // Check exception specifications
8883  if (S.CheckExceptionSpecCompatibility(CurInit.get(), DestType))
8884  return ExprError();
8885 
8886  QualType MTETy = Step->Type;
8887 
8888  // When this is an incomplete array type (such as when this is
8889  // initializing an array of unknown bounds from an init list), use THAT
8890  // type instead so that we propagate the array bounds.
8891  if (MTETy->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
8892  !CurInit.get()->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType() &&
8893  S.Context.hasSameType(
8894  MTETy->getPointeeOrArrayElementType(),
8895  CurInit.get()->getType()->getPointeeOrArrayElementType()))
8896  MTETy = CurInit.get()->getType();
8897 
8898  // Materialize the temporary into memory.
8899  MaterializeTemporaryExpr *MTE = S.CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(
8900  MTETy, CurInit.get(), Entity.getType()->isLValueReferenceType());
8901  CurInit = MTE;
8902 
8903  // If we're extending this temporary to automatic storage duration -- we
8904  // need to register its cleanup during the full-expression's cleanups.
8905  if (MTE->getStorageDuration() == SD_Automatic &&
8906  MTE->getType().isDestructedType())
8907  S.Cleanup.setExprNeedsCleanups(true);
8908  break;
8909  }
8910 
8911  case SK_FinalCopy:
8912  if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
8913  return ExprError();
8914 
8915  // If the overall initialization is initializing a temporary, we already
8916  // bound our argument if it was necessary to do so. If not (if we're
8917  // ultimately initializing a non-temporary), our argument needs to be
8918  // bound since it's initializing a function parameter.
8919  // FIXME: This is a mess. Rationalize temporary destruction.
8920  if (!shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
8921  CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.get());
8922  CurInit = CopyObject(S, Step->Type, Entity, CurInit,
8923  /*IsExtraneousCopy=*/false);
8924  break;
8925 
8926  case SK_ExtraneousCopyToTemporary:
8927  CurInit = CopyObject(S, Step->Type, Entity, CurInit,
8928  /*IsExtraneousCopy=*/true);
8929  break;
8930 
8931  case SK_UserConversion: {
8932  // We have a user-defined conversion that invokes either a constructor
8933  // or a conversion function.
8934  CastKind CastKind;
8935  FunctionDecl *Fn = Step->Function.Function;
8936  DeclAccessPair FoundFn = Step->Function.FoundDecl;
8937  bool HadMultipleCandidates = Step->Function.HadMultipleCandidates;
8938  bool CreatedObject = false;
8939  if (CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Fn)) {
8940  // Build a call to the selected constructor.
8941  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> ConstructorArgs;
8942  SourceLocation Loc = CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc();
8943 
8944  // Determine the arguments required to actually perform the constructor
8945  // call.
8946  Expr *Arg = CurInit.get();
8947  if (S.CompleteConstructorCall(Constructor, Step->Type,
8948  MultiExprArg(&Arg, 1), Loc,
8949  ConstructorArgs))
8950  return ExprError();
8951 
8952  // Build an expression that constructs a temporary.
8953  CurInit = S.BuildCXXConstructExpr(
8954  Loc, Step->Type, FoundFn, Constructor, ConstructorArgs,
8955  HadMultipleCandidates,
8956  /*ListInit*/ false,
8957  /*StdInitListInit*/ false,
8958  /*ZeroInit*/ false, CXXConstructionKind::Complete, SourceRange());
8959  if (CurInit.isInvalid())
8960  return ExprError();
8961 
8962  S.CheckConstructorAccess(Kind.getLocation(), Constructor, FoundFn,
8963  Entity);
8964  if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(FoundFn, Kind.getLocation()))
8965  return ExprError();
8966 
8967  CastKind = CK_ConstructorConversion;
8968  CreatedObject = true;
8969  } else {
8970  // Build a call to the conversion function.
8971  CXXConversionDecl *Conversion = cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Fn);
8972  S.CheckMemberOperatorAccess(Kind.getLocation(), CurInit.get(), nullptr,
8973  FoundFn);
8974  if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(FoundFn, Kind.getLocation()))
8975  return ExprError();
8976 
8977  CurInit = S.BuildCXXMemberCallExpr(CurInit.get(), FoundFn, Conversion,
8978  HadMultipleCandidates);
8979  if (CurInit.isInvalid())
8980  return ExprError();
8981 
8982  CastKind = CK_UserDefinedConversion;
8983  CreatedObject = Conversion->getReturnType()->isRecordType();
8984  }
8985 
8986  if (CreatedObject && checkAbstractType(CurInit.get()->getType()))
8987  return ExprError();
8988 
8989  CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
8990  S.Context, CurInit.get()->getType(), CastKind, CurInit.get(), nullptr,
8991  CurInit.get()->getValueKind(), S.CurFPFeatureOverrides());
8992 
8993  if (shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
8994  // The overall entity is temporary, so this expression should be
8995  // destroyed at the end of its full-expression.
8996  CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.getAs<Expr>());
8997  else if (CreatedObject && shouldDestroyEntity(Entity)) {
8998  // The object outlasts the full-expression, but we need to prepare for
8999  // a destructor being run on it.
9000  // FIXME: It makes no sense to do this here. This should happen
9001  // regardless of how we initialized the entity.
9002  QualType T = CurInit.get()->getType();
9003  if (const RecordType *Record = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
9004  CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor
9005  = S.LookupDestructor(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record->getDecl()));
9006  S.CheckDestructorAccess(CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc(), Destructor,
9007  S.PDiag(diag::err_access_dtor_temp) << T);
9008  S.MarkFunctionReferenced(CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc(), Destructor);
9009  if (S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Destructor, CurInit.get()->getBeginLoc()))
9010  return ExprError();
9011  }
9012  }
9013  break;
9014  }
9015 
9016  case SK_QualificationConversionLValue:
9017  case SK_QualificationConversionXValue:
9018  case SK_QualificationConversionPRValue: {
9019  // Perform a qualification conversion; these can never go wrong.
9020  ExprValueKind VK =
9021  Step->Kind == SK_QualificationConversionLValue
9022  ? VK_LValue
9023  : (Step->Kind == SK_QualificationConversionXValue ? VK_XValue
9024  : VK_PRValue);
9025  CurInit = S.PerformQualificationConversion(CurInit.get(), Step->Type, VK);
9026  break;
9027  }
9028 
9029  case SK_FunctionReferenceConversion:
9030  assert(CurInit.get()->isLValue() &&
9031  "function reference should be lvalue");
9032  CurInit =
9033  S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type, CK_NoOp, VK_LValue);
9034  break;
9035 
9036  case SK_AtomicConversion: {
9037  assert(CurInit.get()->isPRValue() && "cannot convert glvalue to atomic");
9038  CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
9039  CK_NonAtomicToAtomic, VK_PRValue);
9040  break;
9041  }
9042 
9043  case SK_ConversionSequence:
9044  case SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing: {
9045  if (const auto *FromPtrType =
9046  CurInit.get()->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
9047  if (const auto *ToPtrType = Step->Type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
9048  if (FromPtrType->getPointeeType()->hasAttr(attr::NoDeref) &&
9049  !ToPtrType->getPointeeType()->hasAttr(attr::NoDeref)) {
9050  // Do not check static casts here because they are checked earlier
9051  // in Sema::ActOnCXXNamedCast()
9052  if (!Kind.isStaticCast()) {
9053  S.Diag(CurInit.get()->getExprLoc(),
9054  diag::warn_noderef_to_dereferenceable_pointer)
9055  << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
9056  }
9057  }
9058  }
9059  }
9060 
9061  CheckedConversionKind CCK =
9062  Kind.isCStyleCast() ? CheckedConversionKind::CStyleCast
9063  : Kind.isFunctionalCast() ? CheckedConversionKind::FunctionalCast
9064  : Kind.isExplicitCast() ? CheckedConversionKind::OtherCast
9065  : CheckedConversionKind::Implicit;
9066  ExprResult CurInitExprRes =
9067  S.PerformImplicitConversion(CurInit.get(), Step->Type, *Step->ICS,
9068  getAssignmentAction(Entity), CCK);
9069  if (CurInitExprRes.isInvalid())
9070  return ExprError();
9071 
9072  S.DiscardMisalignedMemberAddress(Step->Type.getTypePtr(), CurInit.get());
9073 
9074  CurInit = CurInitExprRes;
9075 
9076  if (Step->Kind == SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing &&
9077  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
9078  DiagnoseNarrowingInInitList(S, *Step->ICS, SourceType, Entity.getType(),
9079  CurInit.get());
9080 
9081  break;
9082  }
9083 
9084  case SK_ListInitialization: {
9085  if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
9086  return ExprError();
9087 
9088  InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(CurInit.get());
9089  // If we're not initializing the top-level entity, we need to create an
9090  // InitializeTemporary entity for our target type.
9091  QualType Ty = Step->Type;
9092  bool IsTemporary = !S.Context.hasSameType(Entity.getType(), Ty);
9093  InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(Ty);
9094  InitializedEntity InitEntity = IsTemporary ? TempEntity : Entity;
9095  InitListChecker PerformInitList(S, InitEntity,
9096  InitList, Ty, /*VerifyOnly=*/false,
9097  /*TreatUnavailableAsInvalid=*/false);
9098  if (PerformInitList.HadError())
9099  return ExprError();
9100 
9101  // Hack: We must update *ResultType if available in order to set the
9102  // bounds of arrays, e.g. in 'int ar[] = {1, 2, 3};'.
9103  // Worst case: 'const int (&arref)[] = {1, 2, 3};'.
9104  if (ResultType &&
9105  ResultType->getNonReferenceType()->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
9106  if ((*ResultType)->isRValueReferenceType())
9107  Ty = S.Context.getRValueReferenceType(Ty);
9108  else if ((*ResultType)->isLValueReferenceType())
9109  Ty = S.Context.getLValueReferenceType(Ty,
9110  (*ResultType)->castAs<LValueReferenceType>()->isSpelledAsLValue());
9111  *ResultType = Ty;
9112  }
9113 
9114  InitListExpr *StructuredInitList =
9115  PerformInitList.getFullyStructuredList();
9116  CurInit.get();
9117  CurInit = shouldBindAsTemporary(InitEntity)
9118  ? S.MaybeBindToTemporary(StructuredInitList)
9119  : StructuredInitList;
9120  break;
9121  }
9122 
9123  case SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList: {
9124  if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
9125  return ExprError();
9126 
9127  // When an initializer list is passed for a parameter of type "reference
9128  // to object", we don't get an EK_Temporary entity, but instead an
9129  // EK_Parameter entity with reference type.
9130  // FIXME: This is a hack. What we really should do is create a user
9131  // conversion step for this case, but this makes it considerably more
9132  // complicated. For now, this will do.
9133  InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(
9134  Entity.getType().getNonReferenceType());
9135  bool UseTemporary = Entity.getType()->isReferenceType();
9136  assert(Args.size() == 1 && "expected a single argument for list init");
9137  InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
9138  S.Diag(InitList->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_cxx98_compat_ctor_list_init)
9139  << InitList->getSourceRange();
9140  MultiExprArg Arg(InitList->getInits(), InitList->getNumInits());
9141  CurInit = PerformConstructorInitialization(S, UseTemporary ? TempEntity :
9142  Entity,
9143  Kind, Arg, *Step,
9144  ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
9145  /*IsListInitialization*/true,
9146  /*IsStdInitListInit*/false,
9147  InitList->getLBraceLoc(),
9148  InitList->getRBraceLoc());
9149  break;
9150  }
9151 
9152  case SK_UnwrapInitList:
9153  CurInit = cast<InitListExpr>(CurInit.get())->getInit(0);
9154  break;
9155 
9156  case SK_RewrapInitList: {
9157  Expr *E = CurInit.get();
9158  InitListExpr *Syntactic = Step->WrappingSyntacticList;
9159  InitListExpr *ILE = new (S.Context) InitListExpr(S.Context,
9160  Syntactic->getLBraceLoc(), E, Syntactic->getRBraceLoc());
9161  ILE->setSyntacticForm(Syntactic);
9162  ILE->setType(E->getType());
9163  ILE->setValueKind(E->getValueKind());
9164  CurInit = ILE;
9165  break;
9166  }
9167 
9168  case SK_ConstructorInitialization:
9169  case SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall: {
9170  if (checkAbstractType(Step->Type))
9171  return ExprError();
9172 
9173  // When an initializer list is passed for a parameter of type "reference
9174  // to object", we don't get an EK_Temporary entity, but instead an
9175  // EK_Parameter entity with reference type.
9176  // FIXME: This is a hack. What we really should do is create a user
9177  // conversion step for this case, but this makes it considerably more
9178  // complicated. For now, this will do.
9179  InitializedEntity TempEntity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(
9180  Entity.getType().getNonReferenceType());
9181  bool UseTemporary = Entity.getType()->isReferenceType();
9182  bool IsStdInitListInit =
9183  Step->Kind == SK_StdInitializerListConstructorCall;
9184  Expr *Source = CurInit.get();
9185  SourceRange Range = Kind.hasParenOrBraceRange()
9186  ? Kind.getParenOrBraceRange()
9187  : SourceRange();
9188  CurInit = PerformConstructorInitialization(
9189  S, UseTemporary ? TempEntity : Entity, Kind,
9190  Source ? MultiExprArg(Source) : Args, *Step,
9191  ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit,
9192  /*IsListInitialization*/ IsStdInitListInit,
9193  /*IsStdInitListInitialization*/ IsStdInitListInit,
9194  /*LBraceLoc*/ Range.getBegin(),
9195  /*RBraceLoc*/ Range.getEnd());
9196  break;
9197  }
9198 
9199  case SK_ZeroInitialization: {
9200  step_iterator NextStep = Step;
9201  ++NextStep;
9202  if (NextStep != StepEnd &&
9203  (NextStep->Kind == SK_ConstructorInitialization ||
9204  NextStep->Kind == SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList)) {
9205  // The need for zero-initialization is recorded directly into
9206  // the call to the object's constructor within the next step.
9207  ConstructorInitRequiresZeroInit = true;
9208  } else if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Value &&
9209  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
9210  !Kind.isImplicitValueInit()) {
9211  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = Entity.getTypeSourceInfo();
9212  if (!TSInfo)
9213  TSInfo = S.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Step->Type,
9214  Kind.getRange().getBegin());
9215 
9216  CurInit = new (S.Context) CXXScalarValueInitExpr(
9217  Entity.getType().getNonLValueExprType(S.Context), TSInfo,
9218  Kind.getRange().getEnd());
9219  } else {
9220  CurInit = new (S.Context) ImplicitValueInitExpr(Step->Type);
9221  }
9222  break;
9223  }
9224 
9225  case SK_CAssignment: {
9226  QualType SourceType = CurInit.get()->getType();
9227 
9228  // Save off the initial CurInit in case we need to emit a diagnostic
9229  ExprResult InitialCurInit = CurInit;
9230  ExprResult Result = CurInit;
9231  Sema::AssignConvertType ConvTy =
9232  S.CheckSingleAssignmentConstraints(Step->Type, Result, true,
9233  Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Parameter_CF_Audited);
9234  if (Result.isInvalid())
9235  return ExprError();
9236  CurInit = Result;
9237 
9238  // If this is a call, allow conversion to a transparent union.
9239  ExprResult CurInitExprRes = CurInit;
9240  if (ConvTy != Sema::Compatible &&
9241  Entity.isParameterKind() &&
9242  S.CheckTransparentUnionArgumentConstraints(Step->Type, CurInitExprRes)
9243  == Sema::Compatible)
9244  ConvTy = Sema::Compatible;
9245  if (CurInitExprRes.isInvalid())
9246  return ExprError();
9247  CurInit = CurInitExprRes;
9248 
9249  if (S.getLangOpts().C23 && initializingConstexprVariable(Entity)) {
9250  CheckC23ConstexprInitConversion(S, SourceType, Entity.getType(),
9251  CurInit.get());
9252 
9253  // C23 6.7.1p6: If an object or subobject declared with storage-class
9254  // specifier constexpr has pointer, integer, or arithmetic type, any
9255  // explicit initializer value for it shall be null, an integer
9256  // constant expression, or an arithmetic constant expression,
9257  // respectively.
9258  Expr::EvalResult ER;
9259  if (Entity.getType()->getAs<PointerType>() &&
9260  CurInit.get()->EvaluateAsRValue(ER, S.Context) &&
9261  !ER.Val.isNullPointer()) {
9262  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_c23_constexpr_pointer_not_null);
9263  }
9264  }
9265 
9266  bool Complained;
9267  if (S.DiagnoseAssignmentResult(ConvTy, Kind.getLocation(),
9268  Step->Type, SourceType,
9269  InitialCurInit.get(),
9270  getAssignmentAction(Entity, true),
9271  &Complained)) {
9272  PrintInitLocationNote(S, Entity);
9273  return ExprError();
9274  } else if (Complained)
9275  PrintInitLocationNote(S, Entity);
9276  break;
9277  }
9278 
9279  case SK_StringInit: {
9280  QualType Ty = Step->Type;
9281  bool UpdateType = ResultType && Entity.getType()->isIncompleteArrayType();
9282  CheckStringInit(CurInit.get(), UpdateType ? *ResultType : Ty,
9283  S.Context.getAsArrayType(Ty), S,
9284  S.getLangOpts().C23 &&
9285  initializingConstexprVariable(Entity));
9286  break;
9287  }
9288 
9289  case SK_ObjCObjectConversion:
9290  CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
9291  CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast,
9292  CurInit.get()->getValueKind());
9293  break;
9294 
9295  case SK_ArrayLoopIndex: {
9296  Expr *Cur = CurInit.get();
9297  Expr *BaseExpr = new (S.Context)
9298  OpaqueValueExpr(Cur->getExprLoc(), Cur->getType(),
9299  Cur->getValueKind(), Cur->getObjectKind(), Cur);
9300  Expr *IndexExpr =
9301  new (S.Context) ArrayInitIndexExpr(S.Context.getSizeType());
9302  CurInit = S.CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(
9303  BaseExpr, Kind.getLocation(), IndexExpr, Kind.getLocation());
9304  ArrayLoopCommonExprs.push_back(BaseExpr);
9305  break;
9306  }
9307 
9308  case SK_ArrayLoopInit: {
9309  assert(!ArrayLoopCommonExprs.empty() &&
9310  "mismatched SK_ArrayLoopIndex and SK_ArrayLoopInit");
9311  Expr *Common = ArrayLoopCommonExprs.pop_back_val();
9312  CurInit = new (S.Context) ArrayInitLoopExpr(Step->Type, Common,
9313  CurInit.get());
9314  break;
9315  }
9316 
9317  case SK_GNUArrayInit:
9318  // Okay: we checked everything before creating this step. Note that
9319  // this is a GNU extension.
9320  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::ext_array_init_copy)
9321  << Step->Type << CurInit.get()->getType()
9322  << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
9323  updateGNUCompoundLiteralRValue(CurInit.get());
9324  [[fallthrough]];
9325  case SK_ArrayInit:
9326  // If the destination type is an incomplete array type, update the
9327  // type accordingly.
9328  if (ResultType) {
9329  if (const IncompleteArrayType *IncompleteDest
9330  = S.Context.getAsIncompleteArrayType(Step->Type)) {
9331  if (const ConstantArrayType *ConstantSource
9332  = S.Context.getAsConstantArrayType(CurInit.get()->getType())) {
9333  *ResultType = S.Context.getConstantArrayType(
9334  IncompleteDest->getElementType(), ConstantSource->getSize(),
9335  ConstantSource->getSizeExpr(), ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
9336  }
9337  }
9338  }
9339  break;
9340 
9341  case SK_ParenthesizedArrayInit:
9342  // Okay: we checked everything before creating this step. Note that
9343  // this is a GNU extension.
9344  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::ext_array_init_parens)
9345  << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
9346  break;
9347 
9348  case SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore:
9349  case SK_PassByIndirectRestore:
9350  checkIndirectCopyRestoreSource(S, CurInit.get());
9351  CurInit = new (S.Context) ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExpr(
9352  CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
9353  Step->Kind == SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore);
9354  break;
9355 
9356  case SK_ProduceObjCObject:
9357  CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
9358  S.Context, Step->Type, CK_ARCProduceObject, CurInit.get(), nullptr,
9359  VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
9360  break;
9361 
9362  case SK_StdInitializerList: {
9363  S.Diag(CurInit.get()->getExprLoc(),
9364  diag::warn_cxx98_compat_initializer_list_init)
9365  << CurInit.get()->getSourceRange();
9366 
9367  // Materialize the temporary into memory.
9368  MaterializeTemporaryExpr *MTE = S.CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(
9369  CurInit.get()->getType(), CurInit.get(),
9370  /*BoundToLvalueReference=*/false);
9371 
9372  // Wrap it in a construction of a std::initializer_list<T>.
9373  CurInit = new (S.Context) CXXStdInitializerListExpr(Step->Type, MTE);
9374 
9375  // Bind the result, in case the library has given initializer_list a
9376  // non-trivial destructor.
9377  if (shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
9378  CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.get());
9379  break;
9380  }
9381 
9382  case SK_OCLSamplerInit: {
9383  // Sampler initialization have 5 cases:
9384  // 1. function argument passing
9385  // 1a. argument is a file-scope variable
9386  // 1b. argument is a function-scope variable
9387  // 1c. argument is one of caller function's parameters
9388  // 2. member initialization from a variable
9389  // 3. variable initialization
9390  // 3a. initializing a file-scope variable
9391  // 3b. initializing a function-scope variable
9392  //
9393  // For file-scope variables, since they cannot be initialized by function
9394  // call of __translate_sampler_initializer in LLVM IR, their references
9395  // need to be replaced by a cast from their literal initializers to
9396  // sampler type. Since sampler variables can only be used in function
9397  // calls as arguments, we only need to replace them when handling the
9398  // argument passing.
9399  assert(Step->Type->isSamplerT() &&
9400  "Sampler initialization on non-sampler type.");
9401  Expr *Init = CurInit.get()->IgnoreParens();
9402  QualType SourceType = Init->getType();
9403  // Case 1
9404  if (Entity.isParameterKind()) {
9405  if (!SourceType->isSamplerT() && !SourceType->isIntegerType()) {
9406  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_sampler_argument_required)
9407  << SourceType;
9408  break;
9409  } else if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Init)) {
9410  auto Var = cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
9411  // Case 1b and 1c
9412  // No cast from integer to sampler is needed.
9413  if (!Var->hasGlobalStorage()) {
9414  CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
9415  S.Context, Step->Type, CK_LValueToRValue, Init,
9416  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
9417  break;
9418  }
9419  // Case 1a
9420  // For function call with a file-scope sampler variable as argument,
9421  // get the integer literal.
9422  // Do not diagnose if the file-scope variable does not have initializer
9423  // since this has already been diagnosed when parsing the variable
9424  // declaration.
9425  if (!Var->getInit() || !isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(Var->getInit()))
9426  break;
9427  Init = cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(const_cast<Expr*>(
9428  Var->getInit()))->getSubExpr();
9429  SourceType = Init->getType();
9430  }
9431  } else if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member &&
9432  !Entity.isImplicitMemberInitializer() &&
9433  !Entity.isDefaultMemberInitializer() &&
9434  isa<DeclRefExpr>(Init)) {
9435  // Case 2: Member initialization from a variable.
9436  CurInit = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(
9437  S.Context, Step->Type, CK_LValueToRValue, Init,
9438  /*BasePath=*/nullptr, VK_PRValue, FPOptionsOverride());
9439  break;
9440  } else {
9441  // Case 3
9442  // Check initializer is 32 bit integer constant.
9443  // If the initializer is taken from global variable, do not diagnose since
9444  // this has already been done when parsing the variable declaration.
9445  if (!Init->isConstantInitializer(S.Context, false))
9446  break;
9447 
9448  if (!SourceType->isIntegerType() ||
9449  32 != S.Context.getIntWidth(SourceType)) {
9450  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_sampler_initializer_not_integer)
9451  << SourceType;
9452  break;
9453  }
9454 
9455  Expr::EvalResult EVResult;
9456  Init->EvaluateAsInt(EVResult, S.Context);
9457  llvm::APSInt Result = EVResult.Val.getInt();
9458  const uint64_t SamplerValue = Result.getLimitedValue();
9459  // 32-bit value of sampler's initializer is interpreted as
9460  // bit-field with the following structure:
9461  // |unspecified|Filter|Addressing Mode| Normalized Coords|
9462  // |31 6|5 4|3 1| 0|
9463  // This structure corresponds to enum values of sampler properties
9464  // defined in SPIR spec v1.2 and also opencl-c.h
9465  unsigned AddressingMode = (0x0E & SamplerValue) >> 1;
9466  unsigned FilterMode = (0x30 & SamplerValue) >> 4;
9467  if (FilterMode != 1 && FilterMode != 2 &&
9468  !S.getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption(
9469  "cl_intel_device_side_avc_motion_estimation", S.getLangOpts()))
9470  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9471  diag::warn_sampler_initializer_invalid_bits)
9472  << "Filter Mode";
9473  if (AddressingMode > 4)
9474  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9475  diag::warn_sampler_initializer_invalid_bits)
9476  << "Addressing Mode";
9477  }
9478 
9479  // Cases 1a, 3a and 3b
9480  // Insert cast from integer to sampler.
9481  CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(Init, S.Context.OCLSamplerTy,
9482  CK_IntToOCLSampler);
9483  break;
9484  }
9485  case SK_OCLZeroOpaqueType: {
9486  assert((Step->Type->isEventT() || Step->Type->isQueueT() ||
9487  Step->Type->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) &&
9488  "Wrong type for initialization of OpenCL opaque type.");
9489 
9490  CurInit = S.ImpCastExprToType(CurInit.get(), Step->Type,
9491  CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType,
9492  CurInit.get()->getValueKind());
9493  break;
9494  }
9495  case SK_ParenthesizedListInit: {
9496  CurInit = nullptr;
9497  TryOrBuildParenListInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, Args, *this,
9498  /*VerifyOnly=*/false, &CurInit);
9499  if (CurInit.get() && ResultType)
9500  *ResultType = CurInit.get()->getType();
9501  if (shouldBindAsTemporary(Entity))
9502  CurInit = S.MaybeBindToTemporary(CurInit.get());
9503  break;
9504  }
9505  }
9506  }
9507 
9508  Expr *Init = CurInit.get();
9509  if (!Init)
9510  return ExprError();
9511 
9512  // Check whether the initializer has a shorter lifetime than the initialized
9513  // entity, and if not, either lifetime-extend or warn as appropriate.
9514  S.checkInitializerLifetime(Entity, Init);
9515 
9516  // Diagnose non-fatal problems with the completed initialization.
9517  if (InitializedEntity::EntityKind EK = Entity.getKind();
9518  (EK == InitializedEntity::EK_Member ||
9519  EK == InitializedEntity::EK_ParenAggInitMember) &&
9520  cast<FieldDecl>(Entity.getDecl())->isBitField())
9521  S.CheckBitFieldInitialization(Kind.getLocation(),
9522  cast<FieldDecl>(Entity.getDecl()), Init);
9523 
9524  // Check for std::move on construction.
9525  CheckMoveOnConstruction(S, Init,
9526  Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result);
9527 
9528  return Init;
9529 }
9530 
9531 /// Somewhere within T there is an uninitialized reference subobject.
9532 /// Dig it out and diagnose it.
9533 static bool DiagnoseUninitializedReference(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
9534  QualType T) {
9535  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
9536  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_reference_without_init)
9537  << T.getNonReferenceType();
9538  return true;
9539  }
9540 
9541  CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
9542  if (!RD || !RD->hasUninitializedReferenceMember())
9543  return false;
9544 
9545  for (const auto *FI : RD->fields()) {
9546  if (FI->isUnnamedBitField())
9547  continue;
9548 
9549  if (DiagnoseUninitializedReference(S, FI->getLocation(), FI->getType())) {
9550  S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_value_initialization_here) << RD;
9551  return true;
9552  }
9553  }
9554 
9555  for (const auto &BI : RD->bases()) {
9556  if (DiagnoseUninitializedReference(S, BI.getBeginLoc(), BI.getType())) {
9557  S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_value_initialization_here) << RD;
9558  return true;
9559  }
9560  }
9561 
9562  return false;
9563 }
9564 
9565 
9566 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9567 // Diagnose initialization failures
9568 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9569 
9570 /// Emit notes associated with an initialization that failed due to a
9571 /// "simple" conversion failure.
9572 static void emitBadConversionNotes(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &entity,
9573  Expr *op) {
9574  QualType destType = entity.getType();
9575  if (destType.getNonReferenceType()->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
9576  op->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
9577 
9578  // Emit a possible note about the conversion failing because the
9579  // operand is a message send with a related result type.
9580  S.EmitRelatedResultTypeNote(op);
9581 
9582  // Emit a possible note about a return failing because we're
9583  // expecting a related result type.
9584  if (entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result)
9585  S.EmitRelatedResultTypeNoteForReturn(destType);
9586  }
9587  QualType fromType = op->getType();
9588  QualType fromPointeeType = fromType.getCanonicalType()->getPointeeType();
9589  QualType destPointeeType = destType.getCanonicalType()->getPointeeType();
9590  auto *fromDecl = fromType->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
9591  auto *destDecl = destType->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
9592  if (fromDecl && destDecl && fromDecl->getDeclKind() == Decl::CXXRecord &&
9593  destDecl->getDeclKind() == Decl::CXXRecord &&
9594  !fromDecl->isInvalidDecl() && !destDecl->isInvalidDecl() &&
9595  !fromDecl->hasDefinition() &&
9596  destPointeeType.getQualifiers().compatiblyIncludes(
9597  fromPointeeType.getQualifiers()))
9598  S.Diag(fromDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_forward_class_conversion)
9599  << S.getASTContext().getTagDeclType(fromDecl)
9600  << S.getASTContext().getTagDeclType(destDecl);
9601 }
9602 
9603 static void diagnoseListInit(Sema &S, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
9604  InitListExpr *InitList) {
9605  QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
9606 
9607  QualType E;
9608  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && S.isStdInitializerList(DestType, &E)) {
9609  QualType ArrayType = S.Context.getConstantArrayType(
9610  E.withConst(),
9611  llvm::APInt(S.Context.getTypeSize(S.Context.getSizeType()),
9612  InitList->getNumInits()),
9613  nullptr, clang::ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
9614  InitializedEntity HiddenArray =
9615  InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(ArrayType);
9616  return diagnoseListInit(S, HiddenArray, InitList);
9617  }
9618 
9619  if (DestType->isReferenceType()) {
9620  // A list-initialization failure for a reference means that we tried to
9621  // create a temporary of the inner type (per [dcl.init.list]p3.6) and the
9622  // inner initialization failed.
9623  QualType T = DestType->castAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
9624  diagnoseListInit(S, InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(T), InitList);
9625  SourceLocation Loc = InitList->getBeginLoc();
9626  if (auto *D = Entity.getDecl())
9627  Loc = D->getLocation();
9628  S.Diag(Loc, diag::note_in_reference_temporary_list_initializer) << T;
9629  return;
9630  }
9631 
9632  InitListChecker DiagnoseInitList(S, Entity, InitList, DestType,
9633  /*VerifyOnly=*/false,
9634  /*TreatUnavailableAsInvalid=*/false);
9635  assert(DiagnoseInitList.HadError() &&
9636  "Inconsistent init list check result.");
9637 }
9638 
9639 bool InitializationSequence::Diagnose(Sema &S,
9640  const InitializedEntity &Entity,
9641  const InitializationKind &Kind,
9642  ArrayRef<Expr *> Args) {
9643  if (!Failed())
9644  return false;
9645 
9646  // When we want to diagnose only one element of a braced-init-list,
9647  // we need to factor it out.
9648  Expr *OnlyArg;
9649  if (Args.size() == 1) {
9650  auto *List = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
9651  if (List && List->getNumInits() == 1)
9652  OnlyArg = List->getInit(0);
9653  else
9654  OnlyArg = Args[0];
9655  }
9656  else
9657  OnlyArg = nullptr;
9658 
9659  QualType DestType = Entity.getType();
9660  switch (Failure) {
9661  case FK_TooManyInitsForReference:
9662  // FIXME: Customize for the initialized entity?
9663  if (Args.empty()) {
9664  // Dig out the reference subobject which is uninitialized and diagnose it.
9665  // If this is value-initialization, this could be nested some way within
9666  // the target type.
9667  assert(Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Value ||
9668  DestType->isReferenceType());
9669  bool Diagnosed =
9670  DiagnoseUninitializedReference(S, Kind.getLocation(), DestType);
9671  assert(Diagnosed && "couldn't find uninitialized reference to diagnose");
9672  (void)Diagnosed;
9673  } else // FIXME: diagnostic below could be better!
9674  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_has_multiple_inits)
9675  << SourceRange(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(), Args.back()->getEndLoc());
9676  break;
9677  case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForReference:
9678  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_list_init_in_parens)
9679  << 1 << Entity.getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9680  break;
9681 
9682  case FK_ArrayNeedsInitList:
9683  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_not_init_list) << 0;
9684  break;
9685  case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrStringLiteral:
9686  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_not_init_list) << 1;
9687  break;
9688  case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrWideStringLiteral:
9689  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_not_init_list) << 2;
9690  break;
9691  case FK_NarrowStringIntoWideCharArray:
9692  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_narrow_string_into_wchar);
9693  break;
9694  case FK_WideStringIntoCharArray:
9695  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_wide_string_into_char);
9696  break;
9697  case FK_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar:
9698  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9699  diag::err_array_init_incompat_wide_string_into_wchar);
9700  break;
9701  case FK_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char:
9702  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9703  diag::err_array_init_plain_string_into_char8_t);
9704  S.Diag(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(),
9705  diag::note_array_init_plain_string_into_char8_t)
9706  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(), "u8");
9707  break;
9708  case FK_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar:
9709  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_array_init_utf8_string_into_char)
9710  << DestType->isSignedIntegerType() << S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20;
9711  break;
9712  case FK_ArrayTypeMismatch:
9713  case FK_NonConstantArrayInit:
9714  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9715  (Failure == FK_ArrayTypeMismatch
9716  ? diag::err_array_init_different_type
9717  : diag::err_array_init_non_constant_array))
9718  << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
9719  << OnlyArg->getType()
9720  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9721  break;
9722 
9723  case FK_VariableLengthArrayHasInitializer:
9724  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_variable_object_no_init)
9725  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9726  break;
9727 
9728  case FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed: {
9729  DeclAccessPair Found;
9730  S.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(OnlyArg,
9731  DestType.getNonReferenceType(),
9732  true,
9733  Found);
9734  break;
9735  }
9736 
9737  case FK_AddressOfUnaddressableFunction: {
9738  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(OnlyArg)->getDecl());
9739  S.checkAddressOfFunctionIsAvailable(FD, /*Complain=*/true,
9740  OnlyArg->getBeginLoc());
9741  break;
9742  }
9743 
9744  case FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed:
9745  case FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed:
9746  switch (FailedOverloadResult) {
9747  case OR_Ambiguous:
9748 
9749  FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
9750  PartialDiagnosticAt(
9751  Kind.getLocation(),
9752  Failure == FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed
9753  ? (S.PDiag(diag::err_typecheck_ambiguous_condition)
9754  << OnlyArg->getType() << DestType
9755  << Args[0]->getSourceRange())
9756  : (S.PDiag(diag::err_ref_init_ambiguous)
9757  << DestType << OnlyArg->getType()
9758  << Args[0]->getSourceRange())),
9759  S, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
9760  break;
9761 
9762  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
9763  auto Cands = FailedCandidateSet.CompleteCandidates(S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
9764  if (!S.RequireCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(),
9765  DestType.getNonReferenceType(),
9766  diag::err_typecheck_nonviable_condition_incomplete,
9767  OnlyArg->getType(), Args[0]->getSourceRange()))
9768  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_typecheck_nonviable_condition)
9769  << (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Result)
9770  << OnlyArg->getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange()
9771  << DestType.getNonReferenceType();
9772 
9773  FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(S, Args, Cands);
9774  break;
9775  }
9776  case OR_Deleted: {
9777  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
9778  OverloadingResult Ovl
9779  = FailedCandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
9780 
9781  StringLiteral *Msg = Best->Function->getDeletedMessage();
9782  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_typecheck_deleted_function)
9783  << OnlyArg->getType() << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
9784  << (Msg != nullptr) << (Msg ? Msg->getString() : StringRef())
9785  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9786  if (Ovl == OR_Deleted) {
9787  S.NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
9788  } else {
9789  llvm_unreachable("Inconsistent overload resolution?");
9790  }
9791  break;
9792  }
9793 
9794  case OR_Success:
9795  llvm_unreachable("Conversion did not fail!");
9796  }
9797  break;
9798 
9799  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary:
9800  if (isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0])) {
9801  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9802  diag::err_lvalue_reference_bind_to_initlist)
9803  << DestType.getNonReferenceType().isVolatileQualified()
9804  << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
9805  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9806  break;
9807  }
9808  [[fallthrough]];
9809 
9810  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToUnrelated:
9811  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
9812  Failure == FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary
9813  ? diag::err_lvalue_reference_bind_to_temporary
9814  : diag::err_lvalue_reference_bind_to_unrelated)
9815  << DestType.getNonReferenceType().isVolatileQualified()
9816  << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
9817  << OnlyArg->getType()
9818  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9819  break;
9820 
9821  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToBitfield: {
9822  // We don't necessarily have an unambiguous source bit-field.
9823  FieldDecl *BitField = Args[0]->getSourceBitField();
9824  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_to_bitfield)
9825  << DestType.isVolatileQualified()
9826  << (BitField ? BitField->getDeclName() : DeclarationName())
9827  << (BitField != nullptr)
9828  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9829  if (BitField)
9830  S.Diag(BitField->getLocation(), diag::note_bitfield_decl);
9831  break;
9832  }
9833 
9834  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToVectorElement:
9835  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_to_vector_element)
9836  << DestType.isVolatileQualified()
9837  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9838  break;
9839 
9840  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToMatrixElement:
9841  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_to_matrix_element)
9842  << DestType.isVolatileQualified() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9843  break;
9844 
9845  case FK_RValueReferenceBindingToLValue:
9846  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_lvalue_to_rvalue_ref)
9847  << DestType.getNonReferenceType() << OnlyArg->getType()
9848  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9849  break;
9850 
9851  case FK_ReferenceAddrspaceMismatchTemporary:
9852  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_temporary_addrspace)
9853  << DestType << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9854  break;
9855 
9856  case FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers: {
9857  QualType SourceType = OnlyArg->getType();
9858  QualType NonRefType = DestType.getNonReferenceType();
9859  Qualifiers DroppedQualifiers =
9860  SourceType.getQualifiers() - NonRefType.getQualifiers();
9861 
9862  if (!NonRefType.getQualifiers().isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(
9863  SourceType.getQualifiers()))
9864  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_drops_quals)
9865  << NonRefType << SourceType << 1 /*addr space*/
9866  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9867  else if (DroppedQualifiers.hasQualifiers())
9868  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_drops_quals)
9869  << NonRefType << SourceType << 0 /*cv quals*/
9870  << Qualifiers::fromCVRMask(DroppedQualifiers.getCVRQualifiers())
9871  << DroppedQualifiers.getCVRQualifiers() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9872  else
9873  // FIXME: Consider decomposing the type and explaining which qualifiers
9874  // were dropped where, or on which level a 'const' is missing, etc.
9875  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_drops_quals)
9876  << NonRefType << SourceType << 2 /*incompatible quals*/
9877  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9878  break;
9879  }
9880 
9881  case FK_ReferenceInitFailed:
9882  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_failed)
9883  << DestType.getNonReferenceType()
9884  << DestType.getNonReferenceType()->isIncompleteType()
9885  << OnlyArg->isLValue()
9886  << OnlyArg->getType()
9887  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9888  emitBadConversionNotes(S, Entity, Args[0]);
9889  break;
9890 
9891  case FK_ConversionFailed: {
9892  QualType FromType = OnlyArg->getType();
9893  PartialDiagnostic PDiag = S.PDiag(diag::err_init_conversion_failed)
9894  << (int)Entity.getKind()
9895  << DestType
9896  << OnlyArg->isLValue()
9897  << FromType
9898  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9899  S.HandleFunctionTypeMismatch(PDiag, FromType, DestType);
9900  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), PDiag);
9901  emitBadConversionNotes(S, Entity, Args[0]);
9902  break;
9903  }
9904 
9905  case FK_ConversionFromPropertyFailed:
9906  // No-op. This error has already been reported.
9907  break;
9908 
9909  case FK_TooManyInitsForScalar: {
9910  SourceRange R;
9911 
9912  auto *InitList = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
9913  if (InitList && InitList->getNumInits() >= 1) {
9914  R = SourceRange(InitList->getInit(0)->getEndLoc(), InitList->getEndLoc());
9915  } else {
9916  assert(Args.size() > 1 && "Expected multiple initializers!");
9917  R = SourceRange(Args.front()->getEndLoc(), Args.back()->getEndLoc());
9918  }
9919 
9920  R.setBegin(S.getLocForEndOfToken(R.getBegin()));
9921  if (Kind.isCStyleOrFunctionalCast())
9922  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_builtin_func_cast_more_than_one_arg)
9923  << R;
9924  else
9925  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_excess_initializers)
9926  << /*scalar=*/2 << R;
9927  break;
9928  }
9929 
9930  case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForScalar:
9931  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_list_init_in_parens)
9932  << 0 << Entity.getType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9933  break;
9934 
9935  case FK_ReferenceBindingToInitList:
9936  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_reference_bind_init_list)
9937  << DestType.getNonReferenceType() << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9938  break;
9939 
9940  case FK_InitListBadDestinationType:
9941  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_init_list_bad_dest_type)
9942  << (DestType->isRecordType()) << DestType << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
9943  break;
9944 
9945  case FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed:
9946  case FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed: {
9947  SourceRange ArgsRange;
9948  if (Args.size())
9949  ArgsRange =
9950  SourceRange(Args.front()->getBeginLoc(), Args.back()->getEndLoc());
9951 
9952  if (Failure == FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed) {
9953  assert(Args.size() == 1 &&
9954  "List construction from other than 1 argument.");
9955  InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
9956  Args = MultiExprArg(InitList->getInits(), InitList->getNumInits());
9957  }
9958 
9959  // FIXME: Using "DestType" for the entity we're printing is probably
9960  // bad.
9961  switch (FailedOverloadResult) {
9962  case OR_Ambiguous:
9963  FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
9964  PartialDiagnosticAt(Kind.getLocation(),
9965  S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_init)
9966  << DestType << ArgsRange),
9967  S, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Args);
9968  break;
9969 
9970  case OR_No_Viable_Function:
9971  if (Kind.getKind() == InitializationKind::IK_Default &&
9972  (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base ||
9973  Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member ||
9974  Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_ParenAggInitMember) &&
9975  isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext)) {
9976  // This is implicit default initialization of a member or
9977  // base within a constructor. If no viable function was
9978  // found, notify the user that they need to explicitly
9979  // initialize this base/member.
9980  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor
9981  = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext);
9982  const CXXRecordDecl *InheritedFrom = nullptr;
9983  if (auto Inherited = Constructor->getInheritedConstructor())
9984  InheritedFrom = Inherited.getShadowDecl()->getNominatedBaseClass();
9985  if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Base) {
9986  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_missing_default_ctor)
9987  << (InheritedFrom ? 2 : Constructor->isImplicit() ? 1 : 0)
9988  << S.Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent())
9989  << /*base=*/0
9990  << Entity.getType()
9991  << InheritedFrom;
9992 
9993  RecordDecl *BaseDecl
9994  = Entity.getBaseSpecifier()->getType()->castAs<RecordType>()
9995  ->getDecl();
9996  S.Diag(BaseDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
9997  << S.Context.getTagDeclType(BaseDecl);
9998  } else {
9999  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_missing_default_ctor)
10000  << (InheritedFrom ? 2 : Constructor->isImplicit() ? 1 : 0)
10001  << S.Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent())
10002  << /*member=*/1
10003  << Entity.getName()
10004  << InheritedFrom;
10005  S.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(),
10006  diag::note_member_declared_at);
10007 
10008  if (const RecordType *Record
10009  = Entity.getType()->getAs<RecordType>())
10010  S.Diag(Record->getDecl()->getLocation(),
10011  diag::note_previous_decl)
10012  << S.Context.getTagDeclType(Record->getDecl());
10013  }
10014  break;
10015  }
10016 
10017  FailedCandidateSet.NoteCandidates(
10018  PartialDiagnosticAt(
10019  Kind.getLocation(),
10020  S.PDiag(diag::err_ovl_no_viable_function_in_init)
10021  << DestType << ArgsRange),
10022  S, OCD_AllCandidates, Args);
10023  break;
10024 
10025  case OR_Deleted: {
10026  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
10027  OverloadingResult Ovl
10028  = FailedCandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
10029  if (Ovl != OR_Deleted) {
10030  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_ovl_deleted_init)
10031  << DestType << ArgsRange;
10032  llvm_unreachable("Inconsistent overload resolution?");
10033  break;
10034  }
10035 
10036  // If this is a defaulted or implicitly-declared function, then
10037  // it was implicitly deleted. Make it clear that the deletion was
10038  // implicit.
10039  if (S.isImplicitlyDeleted(Best->Function))
10040  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_ovl_deleted_special_init)
10041  << llvm::to_underlying(
10042  S.getSpecialMember(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Best->Function)))
10043  << DestType << ArgsRange;
10044  else {
10045  StringLiteral *Msg = Best->Function->getDeletedMessage();
10046  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_ovl_deleted_init)
10047  << DestType << (Msg != nullptr)
10048  << (Msg ? Msg->getString() : StringRef()) << ArgsRange;
10049  }
10050 
10051  S.NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
10052  break;
10053  }
10054 
10055  case OR_Success:
10056  llvm_unreachable("Conversion did not fail!");
10057  }
10058  }
10059  break;
10060 
10061  case FK_DefaultInitOfConst:
10062  if (Entity.getKind() == InitializedEntity::EK_Member &&
10063  isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext)) {
10064  // This is implicit default-initialization of a const member in
10065  // a constructor. Complain that it needs to be explicitly
10066  // initialized.
10067  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(S.CurContext);
10068  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_uninitialized_member_in_ctor)
10069  << (Constructor->getInheritedConstructor() ? 2 :
10070  Constructor->isImplicit() ? 1 : 0)
10071  << S.Context.getTypeDeclType(Constructor->getParent())
10072  << /*const=*/1
10073  << Entity.getName();
10074  S.Diag(Entity.getDecl()->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
10075  << Entity.getName();
10076  } else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast_if_present<VarDecl>(Entity.getDecl());
10077  VD && VD->isConstexpr()) {
10078  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_constexpr_var_requires_const_init)
10079  << VD;
10080  } else {
10081  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_default_init_const)
10082  << DestType << (bool)DestType->getAs<RecordType>();
10083  }
10084  break;
10085 
10086  case FK_Incomplete:
10087  S.RequireCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), FailedIncompleteType,
10088  diag::err_init_incomplete_type);
10089  break;
10090 
10091  case FK_ListInitializationFailed: {
10092  // Run the init list checker again to emit diagnostics.
10093  InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
10094  diagnoseListInit(S, Entity, InitList);
10095  break;
10096  }
10097 
10098  case FK_PlaceholderType: {
10099  // FIXME: Already diagnosed!
10100  break;
10101  }
10102 
10103  case FK_ExplicitConstructor: {
10104  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_selected_explicit_constructor)
10105  << Args[0]->getSourceRange();
10106  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
10107  OverloadingResult Ovl
10108  = FailedCandidateSet.BestViableFunction(S, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
10109  (void)Ovl;
10110  assert(Ovl == OR_Success && "Inconsistent overload resolution");
10111  CXXConstructorDecl *CtorDecl = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Best->Function);
10112  S.Diag(CtorDecl->getLocation(),
10113  diag::note_explicit_ctor_deduction_guide_here) << false;
10114  break;
10115  }
10116 
10117  case FK_ParenthesizedListInitFailed:
10118  TryOrBuildParenListInitialization(S, Entity, Kind, Args, *this,
10119  /*VerifyOnly=*/false);
10120  break;
10121 
10122  case FK_DesignatedInitForNonAggregate:
10123  InitListExpr *InitList = cast<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
10124  S.Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_designated_init_for_non_aggregate)
10125  << Entity.getType() << InitList->getSourceRange();
10126  break;
10127  }
10128 
10129  PrintInitLocationNote(S, Entity);
10130  return true;
10131 }
10132 
10133 void InitializationSequence::dump(raw_ostream &OS) const {
10134  switch (SequenceKind) {
10135  case FailedSequence: {
10136  OS << "Failed sequence: ";
10137  switch (Failure) {
10138  case FK_TooManyInitsForReference:
10139  OS << "too many initializers for reference";
10140  break;
10141 
10142  case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForReference:
10143  OS << "parenthesized list init for reference";
10144  break;
10145 
10146  case FK_ArrayNeedsInitList:
10147  OS << "array requires initializer list";
10148  break;
10149 
10150  case FK_AddressOfUnaddressableFunction:
10151  OS << "address of unaddressable function was taken";
10152  break;
10153 
10154  case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrStringLiteral:
10155  OS << "array requires initializer list or string literal";
10156  break;
10157 
10158  case FK_ArrayNeedsInitListOrWideStringLiteral:
10159  OS << "array requires initializer list or wide string literal";
10160  break;
10161 
10162  case FK_NarrowStringIntoWideCharArray:
10163  OS << "narrow string into wide char array";
10164  break;
10165 
10166  case FK_WideStringIntoCharArray:
10167  OS << "wide string into char array";
10168  break;
10169 
10170  case FK_IncompatWideStringIntoWideChar:
10171  OS << "incompatible wide string into wide char array";
10172  break;
10173 
10174  case FK_PlainStringIntoUTF8Char:
10175  OS << "plain string literal into char8_t array";
10176  break;
10177 
10178  case FK_UTF8StringIntoPlainChar:
10179  OS << "u8 string literal into char array";
10180  break;
10181 
10182  case FK_ArrayTypeMismatch:
10183  OS << "array type mismatch";
10184  break;
10185 
10186  case FK_NonConstantArrayInit:
10187  OS << "non-constant array initializer";
10188  break;
10189 
10190  case FK_AddressOfOverloadFailed:
10191  OS << "address of overloaded function failed";
10192  break;
10193 
10194  case FK_ReferenceInitOverloadFailed:
10195  OS << "overload resolution for reference initialization failed";
10196  break;
10197 
10198  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToTemporary:
10199  OS << "non-const lvalue reference bound to temporary";
10200  break;
10201 
10202  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToBitfield:
10203  OS << "non-const lvalue reference bound to bit-field";
10204  break;
10205 
10206  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToVectorElement:
10207  OS << "non-const lvalue reference bound to vector element";
10208  break;
10209 
10210  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToMatrixElement:
10211  OS << "non-const lvalue reference bound to matrix element";
10212  break;
10213 
10214  case FK_NonConstLValueReferenceBindingToUnrelated:
10215  OS << "non-const lvalue reference bound to unrelated type";
10216  break;
10217 
10218  case FK_RValueReferenceBindingToLValue:
10219  OS << "rvalue reference bound to an lvalue";
10220  break;
10221 
10222  case FK_ReferenceInitDropsQualifiers:
10223  OS << "reference initialization drops qualifiers";
10224  break;
10225 
10226  case FK_ReferenceAddrspaceMismatchTemporary:
10227  OS << "reference with mismatching address space bound to temporary";
10228  break;
10229 
10230  case FK_ReferenceInitFailed:
10231  OS << "reference initialization failed";
10232  break;
10233 
10234  case FK_ConversionFailed:
10235  OS << "conversion failed";
10236  break;
10237 
10238  case FK_ConversionFromPropertyFailed:
10239  OS << "conversion from property failed";
10240  break;
10241 
10242  case FK_TooManyInitsForScalar:
10243  OS << "too many initializers for scalar";
10244  break;
10245 
10246  case FK_ParenthesizedListInitForScalar:
10247  OS << "parenthesized list init for reference";
10248  break;
10249 
10250  case FK_ReferenceBindingToInitList:
10251  OS << "referencing binding to initializer list";
10252  break;
10253 
10254  case FK_InitListBadDestinationType:
10255  OS << "initializer list for non-aggregate, non-scalar type";
10256  break;
10257 
10258  case FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed:
10259  OS << "overloading failed for user-defined conversion";
10260  break;
10261 
10262  case FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed:
10263  OS << "constructor overloading failed";
10264  break;
10265 
10266  case FK_DefaultInitOfConst:
10267  OS << "default initialization of a const variable";
10268  break;
10269 
10270  case FK_Incomplete:
10271  OS << "initialization of incomplete type";
10272  break;
10273 
10274  case FK_ListInitializationFailed:
10275  OS << "list initialization checker failure";
10276  break;
10277 
10278  case FK_VariableLengthArrayHasInitializer:
10279  OS << "variable length array has an initializer";
10280  break;
10281 
10282  case FK_PlaceholderType:
10283  OS << "initializer expression isn't contextually valid";
10284  break;
10285 
10286  case FK_ListConstructorOverloadFailed:
10287  OS << "list constructor overloading failed";
10288  break;
10289 
10290  case FK_ExplicitConstructor:
10291  OS << "list copy initialization chose explicit constructor";
10292  break;
10293 
10294  case FK_ParenthesizedListInitFailed:
10295  OS << "parenthesized list initialization failed";
10296  break;
10297 
10298  case FK_DesignatedInitForNonAggregate:
10299  OS << "designated initializer for non-aggregate type";
10300  break;
10301  }
10302  OS << '\n';
10303  return;
10304  }
10305 
10306  case DependentSequence:
10307  OS << "Dependent sequence\n";
10308  return;
10309 
10310  case NormalSequence:
10311  OS << "Normal sequence: ";
10312  break;
10313  }
10314 
10315  for (step_iterator S = step_begin(), SEnd = step_end(); S != SEnd; ++S) {
10316  if (S != step_begin()) {
10317  OS << " -> ";
10318  }
10319 
10320  switch (S->Kind) {
10321  case SK_ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction:
10322  OS << "resolve address of overloaded function";
10323  break;
10324 
10325  case SK_CastDerivedToBasePRValue:
10326  OS << "derived-to-base (prvalue)";
10327  break;
10328 
10329  case SK_CastDerivedToBaseXValue:
10330  OS << "derived-to-base (xvalue)";
10331  break;
10332 
10333  case SK_CastDerivedToBaseLValue:
10334  OS << "derived-to-base (lvalue)";
10335  break;
10336 
10337  case SK_BindReference:
10338  OS << "bind reference to lvalue";
10339  break;
10340 
10341  case SK_BindReferenceToTemporary:
10342  OS << "bind reference to a temporary";
10343  break;
10344 
10345  case SK_FinalCopy:
10346  OS << "final copy in class direct-initialization";
10347  break;
10348 
10349  case SK_ExtraneousCopyToTemporary:
10350  OS << "extraneous C++03 copy to temporary";
10351  break;
10352 
10353  case SK_UserConversion:
10354  OS << "user-defined conversion via " << *S->Function.Function;
10355  break;
10356 
10357  case SK_QualificationConversionPRValue:
10358  OS << "qualification conversion (prvalue)";
10359  break;
10360 
10361  case SK_QualificationConversionXValue:
10362  OS << "qualification conversion (xvalue)";
10363  break;
10364 
10365  case SK_QualificationConversionLValue:
10366  OS << "qualification conversion (lvalue)";
10367  break;
10368 
10369  case SK_FunctionReferenceConversion:
10370  OS << "function reference conversion";
10371  break;
10372 
10373  case SK_AtomicConversion:
10374  OS << "non-atomic-to-atomic conversion";
10375  break;
10376 
10377  case SK_ConversionSequence:
10378  OS << "implicit conversion sequence (";
10379  S->ICS->dump(); // FIXME: use OS
10380  OS << ")";
10381  break;
10382 
10383  case SK_ConversionSequenceNoNarrowing:
10384  OS << "implicit conversion sequence with narrowing prohibited (";
10385  S->ICS->dump(); // FIXME: use OS
10386  OS << ")";
10387  break;
10388 
10389  case SK_ListInitialization:
10390  OS << "list aggregate initialization";
10391  break;
10392 
10393  case SK_UnwrapInitList:
10394  OS << "unwrap reference initializer list";
10395  break;
10396 
10397  case SK_RewrapInitList:
10398  OS << "rewrap reference initializer list";
10399  break;
10400 
10401  case SK_ConstructorInitialization:
10402  OS << "constructor initialization";
10403  break;
10404 
10405  case SK_ConstructorInitializationFromList:
10406  OS << "list initialization via constructor";
10407  break;
10408 
10409  case SK_ZeroInitialization:
10410  OS << "zero initialization";
10411  break;
10412 
10413  case SK_CAssignment:
10414  OS << "C assignment";
10415  break;
10416 
10417  case SK_StringInit:
10418  OS << "string initialization";
10419  break;
10420 
10421  case SK_ObjCObjectConversion:
10422  OS << "Objective-C object conversion";
10423  break;
10424 
10425  case SK_ArrayLoopIndex:
10426  OS << "indexing for array initialization loop";
10427  break;
10428 
10429  case SK_ArrayLoopInit:
10430  OS << "array initialization loop";
10431  break;
10432 
10433  case SK_ArrayInit:
10434  OS << "array initialization";
10435  break;
10436 
10437  case SK_GNUArrayInit:

10439  break;

10441  case SK_ParenthesizedArrayInit:
10442  OS << "parenthesized array initialization";
10443  break;
10444 
10445  case SK_PassByIndirectCopyRestore:

10447  break;
10448

10451  break;
10452

10455  break;

10459  break;
10460

10471  break;

10474  break;
10475  }
10476 
10477  OS << " [" << S->Type << ']';
10478  }
10479 
10480  OS << '\n';
10481 }

10483 void InitializationSequence::dump() const {
