10486 
10487 static void DiagnoseNarrowingInInitList(Sema &S,
10488  const ImplicitConversionSequence &ICS,
10489  QualType PreNarrowingType,
10490  QualType EntityType,
10491  const Expr *PostInit) {
10492  const StandardConversionSequence *SCS = nullptr;
10493  switch (ICS.getKind()) {
10494  case ImplicitConversionSequence::StandardConversion:
10495  SCS = &ICS.Standard;
10496  break;
10497  case ImplicitConversionSequence::UserDefinedConversion:
10498  SCS = &ICS.UserDefined.After;
10499  break;
10500  case ImplicitConversionSequence::AmbiguousConversion:
10501  case ImplicitConversionSequence::StaticObjectArgumentConversion:
10502  case ImplicitConversionSequence::EllipsisConversion:
10503  case ImplicitConversionSequence::BadConversion:
10504  return;
10505  }
10506 
10507  auto MakeDiag = [&](bool IsConstRef, unsigned DefaultDiagID,
10508  unsigned ConstRefDiagID, unsigned WarnDiagID) {
10509  unsigned DiagID;
10510  auto &L = S.getLangOpts();
10511  if (L.CPlusPlus11 &&
10512  (!L.MicrosoftExt || L.isCompatibleWithMSVC(LangOptions::MSVC2015)))
10513  DiagID = IsConstRef ? ConstRefDiagID : DefaultDiagID;
10514  else
10515  DiagID = WarnDiagID;
10516  return S.Diag(PostInit->getBeginLoc(), DiagID)
10517  << PostInit->getSourceRange();
10518  };
10519 
10520  // C++11 [dcl.init.list]p7: Check whether this is a narrowing conversion.
10521  APValue ConstantValue;
10522  QualType ConstantType;
10523  switch (SCS->getNarrowingKind(S.Context, PostInit, ConstantValue,
10524  ConstantType)) {
10525  case NK_Not_Narrowing:
10526  case NK_Dependent_Narrowing:
10527  // No narrowing occurred.
10528  return;
10529 
10530  case NK_Type_Narrowing: {
10531  // This was a floating-to-integer conversion, which is always considered a
10532  // narrowing conversion even if the value is a constant and can be
10533  // represented exactly as an integer.
10534  QualType T = EntityType.getNonReferenceType();
10535  MakeDiag(T != EntityType, diag::ext_init_list_type_narrowing,
10536  diag::ext_init_list_type_narrowing_const_reference,
10537  diag::warn_init_list_type_narrowing)
10538  << PreNarrowingType.getLocalUnqualifiedType()
10539  << T.getLocalUnqualifiedType();
10540  break;
10541  }
10542 
10543  case NK_Constant_Narrowing: {
10544  // A constant value was narrowed.
10545  MakeDiag(EntityType.getNonReferenceType() != EntityType,
10546  diag::ext_init_list_constant_narrowing,
10547  diag::ext_init_list_constant_narrowing_const_reference,
10548  diag::warn_init_list_constant_narrowing)
10549  << ConstantValue.getAsString(S.getASTContext(), ConstantType)
10550  << EntityType.getNonReferenceType().getLocalUnqualifiedType();
10551  break;
10552  }
10553 
10554  case NK_Variable_Narrowing: {
10555  // A variable's value may have been narrowed.
10556  MakeDiag(EntityType.getNonReferenceType() != EntityType,
10557  diag::ext_init_list_variable_narrowing,
10558  diag::ext_init_list_variable_narrowing_const_reference,
10559  diag::warn_init_list_variable_narrowing)
10560  << PreNarrowingType.getLocalUnqualifiedType()
10561  << EntityType.getNonReferenceType().getLocalUnqualifiedType();
10562  break;
10563  }
10564  }
10565 
10566  SmallString<128> StaticCast;
10567  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(StaticCast);
10568  OS << "static_cast<";
10569  if (const TypedefType *TT = EntityType->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
10570  // It's important to use the typedef's name if there is one so that the
10571  // fixit doesn't break code using types like int64_t.
10572  //
10573  // FIXME: This will break if the typedef requires qualification. But
10574  // getQualifiedNameAsString() includes non-machine-parsable components.
10575  OS << *TT->getDecl();
10576  } else if (const BuiltinType *BT = EntityType->getAs<BuiltinType>())
10577  OS << BT->getName(S.getLangOpts());
10578  else {
10579  // Oops, we didn't find the actual type of the variable. Don't emit a fixit
10580  // with a broken cast.
10581  return;
10582  }
10583  OS << ">(";
10584  S.Diag(PostInit->getBeginLoc(), diag::note_init_list_narrowing_silence)
10585  << PostInit->getSourceRange()
10586  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(PostInit->getBeginLoc(), OS.str())
10587  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
10588  S.getLocForEndOfToken(PostInit->getEndLoc()), ")");
10589 }
10590 
10591 static void CheckC23ConstexprInitConversion(Sema &S, QualType FromType,
10592  QualType ToType, Expr *Init) {
10593  assert(S.getLangOpts().C23);
10594  ImplicitConversionSequence ICS = S.TryImplicitConversion(
10595  Init->IgnoreParenImpCasts(), ToType, /*SuppressUserConversions*/ false,
10596  Sema::AllowedExplicit::None,
10597  /*InOverloadResolution*/ false,
10598  /*CStyle*/ false,
10599  /*AllowObjCWritebackConversion=*/false);
10600 
10601  if (!ICS.isStandard())
10602  return;
10603 
10604  APValue Value;
10605  QualType PreNarrowingType;
10606  // Reuse C++ narrowing check.
10607  switch (ICS.Standard.getNarrowingKind(
10608  S.Context, Init, Value, PreNarrowingType,
10609  /*IgnoreFloatToIntegralConversion*/ false)) {
10610  // The value doesn't fit.
10611  case NK_Constant_Narrowing:
10612  S.Diag(Init->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_c23_constexpr_init_not_representable)
10613  << Value.getAsString(S.Context, PreNarrowingType) << ToType;
10614  return;
10615 
10616  // Conversion to a narrower type.
10617  case NK_Type_Narrowing:
10618  S.Diag(Init->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_c23_constexpr_init_type_mismatch)
10619  << ToType << FromType;
10620  return;
10621 
10622  // Since we only reuse narrowing check for C23 constexpr variables here, we're
10623  // not really interested in these cases.
10624  case NK_Dependent_Narrowing:
10625  case NK_Variable_Narrowing:
10626  case NK_Not_Narrowing:
10627  return;
10628  }
10629  llvm_unreachable("unhandled case in switch");
10630 }
10631 
10632 static void CheckC23ConstexprInitStringLiteral(const StringLiteral *SE,
10633  Sema &SemaRef, QualType &TT) {
10634  assert(SemaRef.getLangOpts().C23);
10635  // character that string literal contains fits into TT - target type.
10636  const ArrayType *AT = SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(TT);
10637  QualType CharType = AT->getElementType();
10638  uint32_t BitWidth = SemaRef.Context.getTypeSize(CharType);
10639  bool isUnsigned = CharType->isUnsignedIntegerType();
10640  llvm::APSInt Value(BitWidth, isUnsigned);
10641  for (unsigned I = 0, N = SE->getLength(); I != N; ++I) {
10642  int64_t C = SE->getCodeUnitS(I, SemaRef.Context.getCharWidth());
10643  Value = C;
10644  if (Value != C) {
10645  SemaRef.Diag(SemaRef.getLocationOfStringLiteralByte(SE, I),
10646  diag::err_c23_constexpr_init_not_representable)
10647  << C << CharType;
10648  return;
10649  }
10650  }
10651  return;
10652 }

10654 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10655 // Initialization helper functions
10656 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10657 bool
10658 Sema::CanPerformCopyInitialization(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
10659  ExprResult Init) {
10660  if (Init.isInvalid())
10661  return false;
10662 
10663  Expr *InitE = Init.get();
10664  assert(InitE && "No initialization expression");
10665 
10666  InitializationKind Kind =
10667  InitializationKind::CreateCopy(InitE->getBeginLoc(), SourceLocation());
10668  InitializationSequence Seq(*this, Entity, Kind, InitE);
10669  return !Seq.Failed();
10670 }
10671 
10672 ExprResult
10673 Sema::PerformCopyInitialization(const InitializedEntity &Entity,
10674  SourceLocation EqualLoc,
10675  ExprResult Init,
10676  bool TopLevelOfInitList,
10677  bool AllowExplicit) {
10678  if (Init.isInvalid())
10679  return ExprError();
10680 
10681  Expr *InitE = Init.get();
10682  assert(InitE && "No initialization expression?");
10683 
10684  if (EqualLoc.isInvalid())
10685  EqualLoc = InitE->getBeginLoc();
10686 
10687  InitializationKind Kind = InitializationKind::CreateCopy(
10688  InitE->getBeginLoc(), EqualLoc, AllowExplicit);
10689  InitializationSequence Seq(*this, Entity, Kind, InitE, TopLevelOfInitList);
10690 
10691  // Prevent infinite recursion when performing parameter copy-initialization.
10692  const bool ShouldTrackCopy =
10693  Entity.isParameterKind() && Seq.isConstructorInitialization();
10694  if (ShouldTrackCopy) {
10695  if (llvm::is_contained(CurrentParameterCopyTypes, Entity.getType())) {
10696  Seq.SetOverloadFailure(
10697  InitializationSequence::FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed,
10698  OR_No_Viable_Function);
10699 
10700  // Try to give a meaningful diagnostic note for the problematic
10701  // constructor.
10702  const auto LastStep = Seq.step_end() - 1;
10703  assert(LastStep->Kind ==
10704  InitializationSequence::SK_ConstructorInitialization);
10705  const FunctionDecl *Function = LastStep->Function.Function;
10706  auto Candidate =
10707  llvm::find_if(Seq.getFailedCandidateSet(),
10708  [Function](const OverloadCandidate &Candidate) -> bool {
10709  return Candidate.Viable &&
10710  Candidate.Function == Function &&
10711  Candidate.Conversions.size() > 0;
10712  });
10713  if (Candidate != Seq.getFailedCandidateSet().end() &&
10714  Function->getNumParams() > 0) {
10715  Candidate->Viable = false;
10716  Candidate->FailureKind = ovl_fail_bad_conversion;
10717  Candidate->Conversions[0].setBad(BadConversionSequence::no_conversion,
10718  InitE,
10719  Function->getParamDecl(0)->getType());
10720  }
10721  }
10722  CurrentParameterCopyTypes.push_back(Entity.getType());
10723  }
10724 
10725  ExprResult Result = Seq.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, InitE);
10726 
10727  if (ShouldTrackCopy)
10728  CurrentParameterCopyTypes.pop_back();
10729 
10730  return Result;
10731 }
10732 
10733 /// Determine whether RD is, or is derived from, a specialization of CTD.
10734 static bool isOrIsDerivedFromSpecializationOf(CXXRecordDecl *RD,
10735  ClassTemplateDecl *CTD) {
10736  auto NotSpecialization = [&] (const CXXRecordDecl *Candidate) {
10737  auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Candidate);
10738  return !CTSD || !declaresSameEntity(CTSD->getSpecializedTemplate(), CTD);
10739  };
10740  return !(NotSpecialization(RD) && RD->forallBases(NotSpecialization));
10741 }
10742 
10743 QualType Sema::DeduceTemplateSpecializationFromInitializer(
10744  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo, const InitializedEntity &Entity,
10745  const InitializationKind &Kind, MultiExprArg Inits) {
10746  auto *DeducedTST = dyn_cast<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(
10747  TSInfo->getType()->getContainedDeducedType());
10748  assert(DeducedTST && "not a deduced template specialization type");
10749 
10750  auto TemplateName = DeducedTST->getTemplateName();
10751  if (TemplateName.isDependent())
10752  return SubstAutoTypeDependent(TSInfo->getType());
10753 
10754  // We can only perform deduction for class templates or alias templates.
10755  auto *Template =
10756  dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateDecl>(TemplateName.getAsTemplateDecl());
10757  TemplateDecl *LookupTemplateDecl = Template;
10758  if (!Template) {
10759  if (auto *AliasTemplate = dyn_cast_or_null<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(
10760  TemplateName.getAsTemplateDecl())) {
10761  Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
10762  diag::warn_cxx17_compat_ctad_for_alias_templates);
10763  LookupTemplateDecl = AliasTemplate;
10764  auto UnderlyingType = AliasTemplate->getTemplatedDecl()
10765  ->getUnderlyingType()
10766  .getCanonicalType();
10767  // C++ [over.match.class.deduct#3]: ..., the defining-type-id of A must be
10768  // of the form
10769  // [typename] [nested-name-specifier] [template] simple-template-id
10770  if (const auto *TST =
10771  UnderlyingType->getAs<TemplateSpecializationType>()) {
10772  Template = dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateDecl>(
10773  TST->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl());
10774  } else if (const auto *RT = UnderlyingType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
10775  // Cases where template arguments in the RHS of the alias are not
10776  // dependent. e.g.
10777  // using AliasFoo = Foo<bool>;
10778  if (const auto *CTSD = llvm::dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(
10779  RT->getAsCXXRecordDecl()))
10780  Template = CTSD->getSpecializedTemplate();
10781  }
10782  }
10783  }
10784  if (!Template) {
10785  Diag(Kind.getLocation(),
10786  diag::err_deduced_non_class_or_alias_template_specialization_type)
10787  << (int)getTemplateNameKindForDiagnostics(TemplateName) << TemplateName;
10788  if (auto *TD = TemplateName.getAsTemplateDecl())
10789  NoteTemplateLocation(*TD);
10790  return QualType();
10791  }
10792 
10793  // Can't deduce from dependent arguments.
10794  if (Expr::hasAnyTypeDependentArguments(Inits)) {
10795  Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
10796  diag::warn_cxx14_compat_class_template_argument_deduction)
10797  << TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange() << 0;
10798  return SubstAutoTypeDependent(TSInfo->getType());
10799  }
10800 
10801  // FIXME: Perform "exact type" matching first, per CWG discussion?
10802  // Or implement this via an implied 'T(T) -> T' deduction guide?
10803 
10804  // FIXME: Do we need/want a std::initializer_list<T> special case?
10805 
10806  // Look up deduction guides, including those synthesized from constructors.
10807  //
10808  // C++1z [over.match.class.deduct]p1:
10809  // A set of functions and function templates is formed comprising:
10810  // - For each constructor of the class template designated by the
10811  // template-name, a function template [...]
10812  // - For each deduction-guide, a function or function template [...]
10813  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(
10814  Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXDeductionGuideName(LookupTemplateDecl),
10815  TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc());
10816  LookupResult Guides(*this, NameInfo, LookupOrdinaryName);
10817  LookupQualifiedName(Guides, LookupTemplateDecl->getDeclContext());
10818 
10819  // FIXME: Do not diagnose inaccessible deduction guides. The standard isn't
10820  // clear on this, but they're not found by name so access does not apply.
10821  Guides.suppressDiagnostics();
10822 
10823  // Figure out if this is list-initialization.
10824  InitListExpr *ListInit =
10825  (Inits.size() == 1 && Kind.getKind() != InitializationKind::IK_Direct)
10826  ? dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Inits[0])
10827  : nullptr;
10828 
10829  // C++1z [over.match.class.deduct]p1:
10830  // Initialization and overload resolution are performed as described in
10831  // [dcl.init] and [over.match.ctor], [over.match.copy], or [over.match.list]
10832  // (as appropriate for the type of initialization performed) for an object
10833  // of a hypothetical class type, where the selected functions and function
10834  // templates are considered to be the constructors of that class type
10835  //
10836  // Since we know we're initializing a class type of a type unrelated to that
10837  // of the initializer, this reduces to something fairly reasonable.
10838  OverloadCandidateSet Candidates(Kind.getLocation(),
10839  OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
10840  OverloadCandidateSet::iterator Best;
10841 
10842  bool AllowExplicit = !Kind.isCopyInit() || ListInit;
10843 
10844  // Return true if the candidate is added successfully, false otherwise.
10845  auto addDeductionCandidate = [&](FunctionTemplateDecl *TD,
10846  CXXDeductionGuideDecl *GD,
10847  DeclAccessPair FoundDecl,
10848  bool OnlyListConstructors,
10849  bool AllowAggregateDeductionCandidate) {
10850  // C++ [over.match.ctor]p1: (non-list copy-initialization from non-class)
10851  // For copy-initialization, the candidate functions are all the
10852  // converting constructors (12.3.1) of that class.
10853  // C++ [over.match.copy]p1: (non-list copy-initialization from class)
10854  // The converting constructors of T are candidate functions.
10855  if (!AllowExplicit) {
10856  // Overload resolution checks whether the deduction guide is declared
10857  // explicit for us.
10858 
10859  // When looking for a converting constructor, deduction guides that
10860  // could never be called with one argument are not interesting to
10861  // check or note.
10862  if (GD->getMinRequiredArguments() > 1 ||
10863  (GD->getNumParams() == 0 && !GD->isVariadic()))
10864  return;
10865  }
10866 
10867  // C++ [over.match.list]p1.1: (first phase list initialization)
10868  // Initially, the candidate functions are the initializer-list
10869  // constructors of the class T
10870  if (OnlyListConstructors && !isInitListConstructor(GD))
10871  return;
10872 
10873  if (!AllowAggregateDeductionCandidate &&
10874  GD->getDeductionCandidateKind() == DeductionCandidate::Aggregate)
10875  return;
10876 
10877  // C++ [over.match.list]p1.2: (second phase list initialization)
10878  // the candidate functions are all the constructors of the class T
10879  // C++ [over.match.ctor]p1: (all other cases)
10880  // the candidate functions are all the constructors of the class of
10881  // the object being initialized
10882 
10883  // C++ [over.best.ics]p4:
10884  // When [...] the constructor [...] is a candidate by
10885  // - [over.match.copy] (in all cases)
10886  // FIXME: The "second phase of [over.match.list] case can also
10887  // theoretically happen here, but it's not clear whether we can
10888  // ever have a parameter of the right type.
10889  bool SuppressUserConversions = Kind.isCopyInit();
10890 
10891  if (TD) {
10892  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> TmpInits;
10893  for (Expr *E : Inits)
10894  if (auto *DI = dyn_cast<DesignatedInitExpr>(E))
10895  TmpInits.push_back(DI->getInit());
10896  else
10897  TmpInits.push_back(E);
10898  AddTemplateOverloadCandidate(
10899  TD, FoundDecl, /*ExplicitArgs=*/nullptr, TmpInits, Candidates,
10900  SuppressUserConversions,
10901  /*PartialOverloading=*/false, AllowExplicit, ADLCallKind::NotADL,
10902  /*PO=*/{}, AllowAggregateDeductionCandidate);
10903  } else {
10904  AddOverloadCandidate(GD, FoundDecl, Inits, Candidates,
10905  SuppressUserConversions,
10906  /*PartialOverloading=*/false, AllowExplicit);
10907  }
10908  };
10909 
10910  bool FoundDeductionGuide = false;
10911 
10912  auto TryToResolveOverload =
10913  [&](bool OnlyListConstructors) -> OverloadingResult {
10914  Candidates.clear(OverloadCandidateSet::CSK_Normal);
10915  bool HasAnyDeductionGuide = false;
10916 
10917  auto SynthesizeAggrGuide = [&](InitListExpr *ListInit) {
10918  auto *Pattern = Template;
10919  while (Pattern->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate()) {
10920  if (Pattern->isMemberSpecialization())
10921  break;
10922  Pattern = Pattern->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate();
10923  }
10924 
10925  auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Pattern->getTemplatedDecl());
10926  if (!(RD->getDefinition() && RD->isAggregate()))
10927  return;
10928  QualType Ty = Context.getRecordType(RD);
10929  SmallVector<QualType, 8> ElementTypes;
10930 
10931  InitListChecker CheckInitList(*this, Entity, ListInit, Ty, ElementTypes);
10932  if (!CheckInitList.HadError()) {
10933  // C++ [over.match.class.deduct]p1.8:
10934  // if e_i is of array type and x_i is a braced-init-list, T_i is an
10935  // rvalue reference to the declared type of e_i and
10936  // C++ [over.match.class.deduct]p1.9:
10937  // if e_i is of array type and x_i is a bstring-literal, T_i is an
10938  // lvalue reference to the const-qualified declared type of e_i and
10939  // C++ [over.match.class.deduct]p1.10:
10940  // otherwise, T_i is the declared type of e_i
10941  for (int I = 0, E = ListInit->getNumInits();
10942  I < E && !isa<PackExpansionType>(ElementTypes[I]); ++I)
10943  if (ElementTypes[I]->isArrayType()) {
10944  if (isa<InitListExpr>(ListInit->getInit(I)))
10945  ElementTypes[I] = Context.getRValueReferenceType(ElementTypes[I]);
10946  else if (isa<StringLiteral>(
10947  ListInit->getInit(I)->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
10948  ElementTypes[I] =
10949  Context.getLValueReferenceType(ElementTypes[I].withConst());
10950  }
10951 
10952  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *TD =
10953  DeclareAggregateDeductionGuideFromInitList(
10954  LookupTemplateDecl, ElementTypes,
10955  TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc())) {
10956  auto *GD = cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(TD->getTemplatedDecl());
10957  addDeductionCandidate(TD, GD, DeclAccessPair::make(TD, AS_public),
10958  OnlyListConstructors,
10959  /*AllowAggregateDeductionCandidate=*/true);
10960  HasAnyDeductionGuide = true;
10961  }
10962  }
10963  };
10964 
10965  for (auto I = Guides.begin(), E = Guides.end(); I != E; ++I) {
10966  NamedDecl *D = (*I)->getUnderlyingDecl();
10967  if (D->isInvalidDecl())
10968  continue;
10969 
10970  auto *TD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D);
10971  auto *GD = dyn_cast_if_present<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(
10972  TD ? TD->getTemplatedDecl() : dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D));
10973  if (!GD)
10974  continue;
10975 
10976  if (!GD->isImplicit())
10977  HasAnyDeductionGuide = true;
10978 
10979  addDeductionCandidate(TD, GD, I.getPair(), OnlyListConstructors,
10980  /*AllowAggregateDeductionCandidate=*/false);
10981  }
10982 
10983  // C++ [over.match.class.deduct]p1.4:
10984  // if C is defined and its definition satisfies the conditions for an
10985  // aggregate class ([dcl.init.aggr]) with the assumption that any
10986  // dependent base class has no virtual functions and no virtual base
10987  // classes, and the initializer is a non-empty braced-init-list or
10988  // parenthesized expression-list, and there are no deduction-guides for
10989  // C, the set contains an additional function template, called the
10990  // aggregate deduction candidate, defined as follows.
10991  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 && !HasAnyDeductionGuide) {
10992  if (ListInit && ListInit->getNumInits()) {
10993  SynthesizeAggrGuide(ListInit);
10994  } else if (Inits.size()) { // parenthesized expression-list
10995  // Inits are expressions inside the parentheses. We don't have
10996  // the parentheses source locations, use the begin/end of Inits as the
10997  // best heuristic.
10998  InitListExpr TempListInit(getASTContext(), Inits.front()->getBeginLoc(),
10999  Inits, Inits.back()->getEndLoc());
11000  SynthesizeAggrGuide(&TempListInit);
11001  }
11002  }
11003 
11004  FoundDeductionGuide = FoundDeductionGuide || HasAnyDeductionGuide;
11005 
11006  return Candidates.BestViableFunction(*this, Kind.getLocation(), Best);
11007  };
11008 
11009  OverloadingResult Result = OR_No_Viable_Function;
11010 
11011  // C++11 [over.match.list]p1, per DR1467: for list-initialization, first
11012  // try initializer-list constructors.
11013  if (ListInit) {
11014  bool TryListConstructors = true;
11015 
11016  // Try list constructors unless the list is empty and the class has one or
11017  // more default constructors, in which case those constructors win.
11018  if (!ListInit->getNumInits()) {
11019  for (NamedDecl *D : Guides) {
11020  auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D->getUnderlyingDecl());
11021  if (FD && FD->getMinRequiredArguments() == 0) {
11022  TryListConstructors = false;
11023  break;
11024  }
11025  }
11026  } else if (ListInit->getNumInits() == 1) {
11027  // C++ [over.match.class.deduct]:
11028  // As an exception, the first phase in [over.match.list] (considering
11029  // initializer-list constructors) is omitted if the initializer list
11030  // consists of a single expression of type cv U, where U is a
11031  // specialization of C or a class derived from a specialization of C.
11032  Expr *E = ListInit->getInit(0);
11033  auto *RD = E->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
11034  if (!isa<InitListExpr>(E) && RD &&
11035  isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), E->getType()) &&
11036  isOrIsDerivedFromSpecializationOf(RD, Template))
11037  TryListConstructors = false;
11038  }
11039 
11040  if (TryListConstructors)
11041  Result = TryToResolveOverload(/*OnlyListConstructor*/true);
11042  // Then unwrap the initializer list and try again considering all
11043  // constructors.
11044  Inits = MultiExprArg(ListInit->getInits(), ListInit->getNumInits());
11045  }
11046 
11047  // If list-initialization fails, or if we're doing any other kind of
11048  // initialization, we (eventually) consider constructors.
11049  if (Result == OR_No_Viable_Function)
11050  Result = TryToResolveOverload(/*OnlyListConstructor*/false);
11051 
11052  switch (Result) {
11053  case OR_Ambiguous:
11054  // FIXME: For list-initialization candidates, it'd usually be better to
11055  // list why they were not viable when given the initializer list itself as
11056  // an argument.
11057  Candidates.NoteCandidates(
11058  PartialDiagnosticAt(
11059  Kind.getLocation(),
11060  PDiag(diag::err_deduced_class_template_ctor_ambiguous)
11061  << TemplateName),
11062  *this, OCD_AmbiguousCandidates, Inits);
11063  return QualType();
11064 
11065  case OR_No_Viable_Function: {
11066  CXXRecordDecl *Primary =
11067  cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(Template)->getTemplatedDecl();
11068  bool Complete =
11069  isCompleteType(Kind.getLocation(), Context.getTypeDeclType(Primary));
11070  Candidates.NoteCandidates(
11071  PartialDiagnosticAt(
11072  Kind.getLocation(),
11073  PDiag(Complete ? diag::err_deduced_class_template_ctor_no_viable
11074  : diag::err_deduced_class_template_incomplete)
11075  << TemplateName << !Guides.empty()),
11076  *this, OCD_AllCandidates, Inits);
11077  return QualType();
11078  }
11079 
11080  case OR_Deleted: {
11081  // FIXME: There are no tests for this diagnostic, and it doesn't seem
11082  // like we ever get here; attempts to trigger this seem to yield a
11083  // generic c'all to deleted function' diagnostic instead.
11084  Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_deduced_class_template_deleted)
11085  << TemplateName;
11086  NoteDeletedFunction(Best->Function);
11087  return QualType();
11088  }
11089 
11090  case OR_Success:
11091  // C++ [over.match.list]p1:
11092  // In copy-list-initialization, if an explicit constructor is chosen, the
11093  // initialization is ill-formed.
11094  if (Kind.isCopyInit() && ListInit &&
11095  cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(Best->Function)->isExplicit()) {
11096  bool IsDeductionGuide = !Best->Function->isImplicit();
11097  Diag(Kind.getLocation(), diag::err_deduced_class_template_explicit)
11098  << TemplateName << IsDeductionGuide;
11099  Diag(Best->Function->getLocation(),
11100  diag::note_explicit_ctor_deduction_guide_here)
11101  << IsDeductionGuide;
11102  return QualType();
11103  }
11104 
11105  // Make sure we didn't select an unusable deduction guide, and mark it
11106  // as referenced.
11107  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Best->FoundDecl, Kind.getLocation());
11108  MarkFunctionReferenced(Kind.getLocation(), Best->Function);
11109  break;
11110  }
11111 
11112  // C++ [dcl.type.class.deduct]p1:
11113  // The placeholder is replaced by the return type of the function selected
11114  // by overload resolution for class template deduction.
11115  QualType DeducedType =
11116  SubstAutoType(TSInfo->getType(), Best->Function->getReturnType());
11117  Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
11118  diag::warn_cxx14_compat_class_template_argument_deduction)
11119  << TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange() << 1 << DeducedType;
11120 
11121  // Warn if CTAD was used on a type that does not have any user-defined
11122  // deduction guides.
11123  if (!FoundDeductionGuide) {
11124  Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
11125  diag::warn_ctad_maybe_unsupported)
11126  << TemplateName;
11127  Diag(Template->getLocation(), diag::note_suppress_ctad_maybe_unsupported);
11128  }
11129 
11130  return DeducedType;
11131 }
